reviews/originality/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges-95d52440abfccb6a.json:131:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The audit found strong near-neighbors in Smith on Nagarjuna and Wittgenstein, Sells on apophatic unsaying, Pargament agency and coping styles, spiritual materialism, spiritual bypassing, VCE and Cheetah House adverse meditation support, and multiple prior Lumenary audits. Full source reliability still requires reading upaya scholarship, Zen post-kensho training, Shinran scholarship, spiritual direction ethics, and practitioner manuals in original languages where possible.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges-95d52440abfccb6a.json:132:    "structural_observation": "MN 22 is a direct near-neighbor for proper use followed by release, but it also requires right grasp before release. The Heart Sutra denies attainment while retaining reliance and mantra, so undermining a result does not imply abandoning the method. Dogen strains the whole stage-completion frame because practice and realization are not cleanly separable. Tannisho strains practitioner-owned authority because nembutsu is presented as free of self-power and not a good act or practice from the practitioner's side. Together, the primary texts support a scoped coding heuristic, not a discovery-level doctrine."
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges-95d52440abfccb6a.json:144:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike MN 22, Smith, Sells, Pargament, spiritual-materialism warnings, VCE safety work, and prior Lumenary return or custody audits, this idea says that the specific interaction between boundary operation and post-threshold custody should predict when a helpful method becomes guidance, conduct, external accountability, rest, or a private judge of worth. That is a useful synthesis, but the structure is mostly inherited from recent internal records."
