reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:161:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The search found strong near-neighbors in transfer-of-training theory, Barnett and Ceci's far-transfer taxonomy, Hadot on school-shaped spiritual exercises, Katz on tradition-conditioned experience, Lindbeck on doctrine as grammar, Pargament on agency allocation, situated learning, Buddhist upaya, and VCE adverse-effects coding. It did not yet close-read full books by Hadot, Katz, Sharf, Lindbeck, Lave and Wenger, or Pargament, and it did not code actual cross-training cases.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:162:    "structural_observation": "SN 45.8 presents path factors as trainable functions, including right view, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. Dogen's Bendowa makes zazen not merely one transferable technique but the expression of the Way itself, where practice and realization are not cleanly separated. The pair supports the candidate's distinction between repeated operation and practice grammar. Similar sitting or effort can have different meaning, authority, and endpoint structures."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:171:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike transfer theory, Hadot, Katz, Lindbeck, Pargament, upaya, VCE, and prior Lumenary ledgers, this idea says grain is only the predictive surplus of a prior dissolution target after rehearsed operation and receiving claimant grammar have already explained what they can."
observations/codex/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate.md:20:- Challenger revision pressure: non-instrumental traditions such as Dogen practice-realization and Shinran no-calculation require a scope gate before result custody language is applied.
observations/codex/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate.md:61:- Add source coding for whether return language is native, permitted, or imported in Dogen, Shinran, MN 22, Heart Sutra, Rinzai, and comparable Christian or Sufi materials.
findings/convergences/2026-05-26-can-native-verification-or-authority-boundaries-be-identified-non-circularly-acro.md:9:Both agents agree that the original typology was too stable and that translation strain requires decomposition by stage, genre, metaphysical register, institutional form, and practice context. They also converge on Dogen's practice-realization identity as a genuine fourth configuration and on the need to test whether reflexive operations predict verification and transmission after controls.
findings/convergences/2026-05-26-whether-allocation-rules-around-convergence-loci-have-genuine-predictive-power-ac.md:13:Whether allocation rules around convergence loci have genuine predictive power across traditions, or whether they are only a descriptive vocabulary applied after the fact. The proponent predicts that coding manuals and practitioner reports by function, holder, forbidden claimant, and transfer moment will predict where warnings cluster, how effort is framed, what counts as error, and how verification is authorized. The challenger predicts that institutional form, teacher authority, ritual system, or historical polemic may explain these features equally well or better. A coded-corpus comparison across Theravada, Advaita, Soto, Dzogchen, Jodo Shinshu, Sufi fana, and apophatic Christian contemplation, testing whether allocation rules outperform rival variables in held-out traditions, would settle it.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges.md:25:- Hybrid anomaly pressure: Dogen practice-realization, Rinzai post-kensho curriculum, Heart Sutra practice after no attainment, and Shinran's Other Power.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges.md:31:The model may still overfit traditions that treat practice as a tool. Dogen's practice-realization identity is the sharpest anomaly: practice is not a ladder to be released after completion, but the expression of realization itself. Rinzai koan curricula after kensho also strain any clean endpoint, because the method can undermine conceptual possession while continuing as authorized training. Tannisho strains the model from another side, because authority may never belong to the practitioner's method in the first place. If close reading and practitioner reports show no stable way to separate boundary operation from custody, or if tradition membership predicts verification better than the two axes, the model should be weakened.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges.md:83:Survived critique from MN 22's validated-then-abandoned raft, Heart Sutra's no-attainment-with-practice hybrid, prior-art pressure from Nagarjuna and Wittgenstein as therapeutic method, and the Dogen and Tannisho anomalies. The claim was narrowed from a broad method-completion typology into a two-axis custody model.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges.md:166:- Result: Pending. MN 22 and the Heart Sutra already suggest boundary pressure, while Dogen and Tannisho may violate simple release models.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges.md:193:- Close-read MN 22, the Heart Sutra, Mandukya Upanishad, Dogen's Genjokoan, Rinzai post-kensho training accounts, and Tannisho for explicit signs of what may guide the practitioner after insight.
findings/convergences/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-careful-tradi.md:13:Does the revised two-layer model produce comparative insight beyond careful tradition-specific reading, and can it map interface risks without reproducing the calculating or dualistic stance that traditions such as Shinran's Other Power, Dzogchen, and practice-realization warn against?
findings/convergences/2026-05-30-two-cruxes-remain-open-first-the-human-condition-crux-does-any-self-administer.md:13:Two cruxes remain open. First, the human-condition crux: does any self-administered safety routing reduce verdict-making, or does the act of self-classifying (evidence or not, instrumental or autotelic, scrupulous or not) merely relocate the verdict onto whether one sorted and returned correctly, feeding the very self-surveillance the teaching means to relieve. Second, the originality crux: once the warrant attaches only to conduct and relationship, is this still a teaching about silence-as-evidence, or has it become the near-general rule that no inner state licenses harm to conduct and care, with the Upanishad, sutta, Dogen, and Shinran sources decorating rather than grounding it. Neither was settled in dialogue; both are routed to a blind coding test and a stratified pilot.
