reviews/originality/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain-63091c8c41cd9e28.json:149:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.74 to about 0.57. The candidate is useful and testable, but its core pieces are strongly anticipated by prior Lumenary entry ledgers, Rambo's conversion model, Lofland-Stark recruitment studies, rites-of-passage and liminality theory, Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar, Freiberger and J. Z. Smith on comparative method, comparative theology, Smart's dimensional analysis, OCIA catechumenate practice, and legitimate peripheral participation. The remaining contribution is the explicit paired-record rule: entry grammar plus preserve-bend-drop translation strain, tested for incremental prediction of safeguards and beginner warnings.",
