reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:133:      "source": "Lindahl et al., The Varieties of Contemplative Experience, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:148:    "Compare predictive value against Rambo conversion stages, Lofland-Stark conversion conditions, Van Gennep and Turner liminality, Lindbeck doctrine-as-grammar, Pargament agency styles, Lave and Wenger legitimate peripheral participation, upaya pedagogy, religious socialization, VCE factor coding, transformative learning theory, and prior Lumenary ledgers.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:149:    "Test six initial cases: Theravada sangha entry, Confucian cultivation, Jodo Shinshu, Augustinian grace, Zen great doubt, and Dzogchen pointing-out.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:154:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.82 to about 0.54. The four-field compression is useful, but most components have strong near-neighbors in prior Lumenary audits, conversion theory, rites-of-passage theory, doctrine-as-grammar, religious problem-solving styles, legitimate peripheral participation, grace theology, Pure Land Other Power, Dogen practice-realization, VCE factor coding, and Meno-style inquiry paradoxes. The remaining contribution is a conditional first-break rule plus a split-source predictive test, not a discovery-level doctrine candidate.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:171:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:183:      "Dogen shusho itto source from Soto Zen, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:186:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The audit checked accessible primary translations, local prior Lumenary audits, and open sources on conversion, liminality, doctrine-as-grammar, religious coping, legitimate peripheral participation, contemplative adverse effects, grace, Other Power, and practice-realization. It did not fully review Rambo's full monograph, Lindbeck's full book, Japanese, Pali, Sanskrit, Tibetan, Latin, or Chinese originals, Shinran scholarship, Dogen scholarship, Sufi bayah and fana sources, Dzogchen pointing-out manuals, or practitioner interviews.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:187:    "structural_observation": "Orange is a near-exact high-severity case: prayer, will, desire, assent, and the beginning of faith are attributed to grace, not unaided nature. Tannisho supplies a vow-held analogue, where entrusting to Amida's Primal Vow displaces self-power and reshapes warning language. SN 22.59 does not fit the same entry grammar, because it negates ownership of aggregates and moves through disenchantment and release without clearly requiring an external break mechanism. Dogen is the strongest anomaly: practice and realization are treated as one, and beginner practice is already implicated in realization, so entry and fruition cannot be cleanly sequenced as threshold and later attainment."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:196:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Rambo, Lofland-Stark, Van Gennep, Turner, Lindbeck, Pargament, Lave and Wenger, Orange, Shinran, Dogen, VCE, Meno-style inquiry paradoxes, and prior Lumenary entry-residue records, this idea says entry should be coded through four interacting fields, incapacity, minimum participation, break mechanism, and residue policy, and that first-break type becomes irreducible only where a tradition denies that ordinary self-generated threshold entry can found the path."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Dogen's practice-realization and other no-boundary traditions where decisive transformation is not approached through a separable practitioner-event interface.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:34:      "expected_observation": "Dzogchen and Mahamudra materials should warn especially against misrecognition, mistaking an experience for recognition, reifying awareness, inadequate teacher relation, and failure to integrate conduct.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:40:      "expected_observation": "Dogen and Soto materials should correct before-after, means-end, and practitioner-event separations more often than texts framed by gradual effort, vow, grace, or recognition.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:46:      "expected_observation": "Independent coders should infer later manual warnings from early register statements at above-chance rates, for example calculation in Shinran, misrecognition in Dzogchen, wrong effort in gradual paths, and conceptual reification in apophatic or raft-like traditions.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:49:      "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Predictions are vague, post hoc, low agreement, or no better than Pargament-style agency categories, direct textual summary, or broad tradition labels."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:57:    "Dogen Bendowa practice-realization training and enlightenment are one text",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:63:    "Pargament religion problem-solving process three styles of coping",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:64:    "Lindbeck Nature of Doctrine cultural linguistic model doctrine rules"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:92:      "difference": "Lindbeck is a theology of doctrine and ecumenical interpretation, not a coding method for transformation registers and failure warnings across practice manuals.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:94:      "overlap": "Close. Lindbeck's cultural-linguistic approach treats doctrines as rules within religious communities, which anticipates the idea that transformation claims must be read inside their own grammar.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:95:      "source": "George Lindbeck, The Nature of Doctrine, cultural-linguistic model, https://openlibrary.org/works/OL5607588W/The_nature_of_doctrine"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:98:      "difference": "Pargament is psychological and coping-focused. The candidate uses primary-text registers of salvation, awakening, or realization and asks what vulnerabilities each tradition itself names.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:100:      "overlap": "Close for agency distribution. Pargament already distinguishes self-directing, deferring, and collaborative religious problem-solving styles involving different relationships between person and God.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:101:      "source": "Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:110:      "difference": "Dzogchen sources provide one register and its risks. The candidate compares that register with Other Power, practice-realization, divine restoration, and effortful paths without reducing them to one agency model.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:113:      "source": "Dzogchen pointing-out practitioner sources, example Tergar on pointing out true nature, https://learning.tergar.org/course_library/mingyur-rinpoches-monthly-teachings/mt-august-2019-pointing-out-your-true-nature/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:120:    "Test primary texts before broad tradition labels: Tannisho chapters 1, 6, 8, 10, and 11; Shinran letters; Bendowa or Genjokoan; one Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out manual; one Christian grace or apophatic source; and one Sufi fana or baqa source.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:123:    "Read Freiberger, Clooney, Hedges, Katz, Sharf, Lindbeck, Pargament, Shinran scholarship, Dogen practice-realization scholarship, upaya literature, and apophatic theology before raising novelty above extended."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:125:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.68 to about 0.56. The register-first discipline is strongly anticipated by comparative theology, hermeneutics, contextualist mysticism scholarship, Lindbeck's cultural-linguistic model, Sharf's critique of generic experience, Pargament's agency styles, Shinran's Other Power, Dogen's practice-realization, and MN 22's self-limiting doctrine use. The remaining contribution is a useful operational extension with predictive fields, not a discovery.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:138:      "Soto Zen teachers familiar with Dogen's practice-realization",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:139:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:148:      "Dogen, Bendowa, especially sections 3, 4, 7, and 10, https://www.abuddhistlibrary.com/Buddhism/C%20-%20Zen/Ancestors/Dogen/Bendowa/Bendowa.htm"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:151:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The closest scholarly prior art includes Oliver Freiberger on comparison as selection, description, juxtaposition, redescription, rectification, and theory formation; Paul Hedges on comparative theology and hermeneutics; Francis Clooney's comparative theology; Katz and Sharf on contextualist and anti-experience-flattening method; Lindbeck's cultural-linguistic model; and Pargament's religious problem-solving styles. The audit did not fully close-read Clooney, Lindbeck, Dzogchen root texts, Meister Eckhart, Qushayri, Ibn Arabi, or Shinran's letters. That gap prevents any candidate-discovery claim.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:152:    "structural_observation": "The Tannisho strongly supports the register-first move. Its decisive register is Other Power, and it names boundary failures such as self-power, calculation, doubt, wrong teacher ownership, and confusing nembutsu with the practitioner's own good act. Bendowa is the anomaly case. It names wrong understanding, false teachers, verbal clinging, and inadequate practice, but its register is practice-realization, where training and enlightenment are not two. The proposed model reads Shinran well, but its interface language strains Dogen because an interface can imply the very separation between practitioner, practice, and realization that Bendowa rejects."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.json:161:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Freiberger, Clooney, Hedges, Katz, Sharf, Lindbeck, Pargament, Shinran, Dogen, and MN 22, this idea claims that comparative work should use a specific two-layer rubric: preserve the transformation register first, then code only tradition-named vulnerabilities, safeguards, and warnings against the rubric itself. Its contribution is operational and predictive, not the discovery that traditions have different registers."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion-54774578d7528e56.md:19:- Zhuangzi, Dzogchen, and Sufi fana are classified as self-dissolving because the practitioner or frame of method becomes irrelevant.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion-54774578d7528e56.md:30:Secondary literature gap: I did not find an exact three-type typology of contemplative methods as confirming, canceling, and dissolving at completion. But the self-canceling portion has very strong prior art in Nagarjuna, Wittgenstein ladder readings, Buddhist raft discussions, and Sells on apophatic unsaying. The dissolving portion is also standard in fana, zuowang, and Dzogchen descriptions. The new part is the comparative axis and its predicted consequences, not the individual patterns.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion-54774578d7528e56.md:69:- If: Dual-trained practitioners should report different relations to their own insight when switching method-types. Then: After Advaita inquiry, practitioners describe recognition as stable witness or Self. After Heart Sutra or Madhyamaka practice, they resist treating any insight as an attained object. After Dzogchen or fana language, they emphasize effortless presence or transformed embodiment over method success. Weakens if: Practitioners report no stable difference, or differences track teacher personality and institutional context more than method-type. Test surface: Structured interviews with practitioners trained in more than one contemplative lineage.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion-54774578d7528e56.md:70:- If: Hybrid traditions should show explicit boundary management between method stages. Then: Texts should mark when to use, trust, undermine, release, or embody a method. Examples would include raft language, preliminary versus main practice, koan curriculum before and after kensho, or thorn-removing-thorn metaphors. Weakens if: No boundary markers appear, or methods freely confirm, cancel, and dissolve without any pedagogical distinction. Test surface: Historical and textual analysis of Zen, Dzogchen, Advaita, Madhyamaka, Sufi, and Christian apophatic training sequences.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion-54774578d7528e56.md:78:- Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-help-should-not-be-managed-fa2107c4aba3ff90.md:26:- Dogen practice-realization sources such as Bendowa or Genjokoan; Shinran and Tannisho Other Power sources, including https://shinranworks.com/commentaries/notes-on-once-calling-and-many-calling/ and Tannisho chapter 8 translations.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-help-should-not-be-managed-fa2107c4aba3ff90.md:28:Structural observation: MN 22 supports a tool-use and non-clinging pattern: a teaching can be used for crossing and then not possessed. The Heart Sutra strains a simple release rule because it denies attainment while preserving reliance on prajnaparamita. Dogen-style practice-realization strains it further because practice is not merely an instrument awaiting later review. Shinran Other Power also resists practitioner-owned handling because merit and final efficacy are not primarily self-managed. The candidate's strongest move is not method-release, which is old, but the fit gate that asks whether ownership, temporality, and available agency exist before prescribing review.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-help-should-not-be-managed-fa2107c4aba3ff90.md:30:Secondary literature gap: The audit still needs direct term-level work on Shinran's jinen honi and hakarai, Dogen's shusho-itto or practice-realization, apophatic unsaying, spiritual direction ethics, and ACT or CBT literature on self-monitoring. Source reliability is adequate for lowering novelty, not for promoting the model as a discovery.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-help-should-not-be-managed-fa2107c4aba3ff90.md:36:- Pargament religion problem-solving process three styles of coping self-directing deferring collaborative
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-help-should-not-be-managed-fa2107c4aba3ff90.md:40:- Dogen practice realization no gaining Bendowa Genjokoan
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-help-should-not-be-managed-fa2107c4aba3ff90.md:48:- Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, 1988, indexed at https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/.: overlap: Close on agency location. Self-directing, deferring, and collaborative religious coping already analyze whether the person, God, or both carry problem-solving responsibility.; difference: Pargament is broader coping theory, not a practice-ending fit gate for contemplative methods after they help.; novelty impact: Strong reduction for agency-location novelty, partial preservation for timing and contraindication.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-help-should-not-be-managed-fa2107c4aba3ff90.md:58:Unlike Pargament's agency styles, ACT's critique of internal control, Buddhist non-grasping, apophatic unsaying, Cheetah House safety routing, and prior Lumenary correction-holder records, this idea says that after-use review itself should be blocked unless three fit conditions are present: provisional ownership, a permitted after, and spare agency. That is useful, but mostly an extension of known parts.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-help-should-not-be-managed-fa2107c4aba3ff90.md:64:Why it strains the model: The idea assumes that private review is often the burden for depleted over-managers. If structure and review are the relieving container, then the model confuses over-management with the absence of safe holding. It also fails if Other Power, Dogen practice-realization, or community-held practice includes rigorous review, conduct correction, and formal repetition without harming agency.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-help-should-not-be-managed-fa2107c4aba3ff90.md:70:- If: Ownership, completion temporality, and spare agency are real fit variables for after-use practices. Then: Split-source coding of primary manuals will show that traditions without practitioner-owned result or discrete after have different warning, verification, and repair patterns than traditions that permit method-use and later handling. Weakens if: Coders cleanly apply keep, release, and embody axes across Shinran, Dogen, Heart Sutra, MN 22, and apophatic sources without distortion, and the three fit variables do not predict held-out warnings or repairs. Test surface: Pre-registered comparative codebook with held-out manual warnings and practitioner interviews.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-help-should-not-be-managed-fa2107c4aba3ff90.md:114:Novelty adjustment: Lower novelty from 0.36 to 0.31. The contribution is a useful scoped fit gate, but it heavily overlaps prior Lumenary holder-routing records, Pargament agency styles, ACT, rumination and self-focused attention research, Buddhist non-grasping, apophatic unsaying, and meditation-safety routing. Publishability should remain modest until the model shows predictive gain over ordinary discernment, spiritual direction, ACT, and clinical triage. Human-condition fit is clear but narrow: burned-out over-managers, compulsive self-monitors, and people with achievement-contingent self-worth. It is not for under-reflectors, acute grief, crisis, severe depression, dissociation, mania, addiction withdrawal, abusive authority contexts, or cases needing accountability and material help.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Dogen's Bendowa practice-realization, especially the claim that training and enlightenment are not two, https://www.abuddhistlibrary.com/Buddhism/C%20-%20Zen/Ancestors/Dogen/Bendowa/Bendowa.htm",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.json:5:    "confidence_effect": "Lowers confidence in the model as a universal explanatory structure. It remains useful as a comparative heuristic, but the anomaly blocks promotion above novel_synthesis until Dogen, Pure Land, Dzogchen, and Christian grace cases are coded without distortion.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If practice and realization are one, then load-transfer language can create the separation Dogen rejects. Zazen is not simply practitioner agency carrying a burden, nor divine or vow relocation. It is enactment of realization. The ledger can handle this only by adding values such as no-transfer, no-boundary, and analyst-frame-refused. Those values may save accuracy but weaken explanatory compression."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.json:31:      "test_surface": "Blind coding trial across SN 45.8, Tannisho, Bendowa, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra manual, one Christian grace manual, and one Sufi fana or baqa source.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.json:32:      "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Scalar maturity, broad tradition labels, or Pargament-style agency locus predict the same warnings as well as the vector ledger, or coders cannot agree on direction and locus."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.json:37:      "test_surface": "Structured interviews with dual-trained practitioners in Theravada and Pure Land, Advaita and bhakti, Zen and Dzogchen or Mahamudra, plus teacher reports of student switching failures.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.json:47:      "expected_observation": "Jodo Shinshu, Dzogchen, Mahamudra, and Christian grace teachers should accept some functional preconditions while objecting to capacity ownership language. Their corrections should cluster around vow-held, teacher-held, grace-held, recognition-event, and analyst-frame-refused values.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.json:56:    "Pargament religion problem-solving process three styles of coping self-directing deferring collaborative",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.json:68:    "Dogen Bendowa practice realization enlightenment are one text translation",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.json:73:      "difference": "Pargament studies coping and divine-human problem solving, not a cross-tradition ledger of receiving, agency, memory, reflexivity, and integration across soteriologies.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.json:75:      "overlap": "Very close for locus and direction. Pargament already distinguishes self-directing, deferring, and collaborative religious problem-solving styles by the relationship between person and God, and ties those styles to competence and religiousness.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.json:76:      "source": "Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.json:94:      "source": "Lindahl et al., The varieties of contemplative experience, PLOS ONE, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.json:131:    "Close-read Shinran's Tannisho and letters, SN 45.8, Bendowa or Genjokoan, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out manual, one Christian grace text, and one Sufi fana or baqa source before public use.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.json:133:    "Run an inter-rater trial comparing the vector ledger against scalar capacity, Pargament agency styles, and VCE-style practice, practitioner, relationship, and context variables.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.json:137:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.70 to about 0.61. The scalar-to-vector move is useful, but its parts are strongly anticipated by Pargament's agency styles, Engler's developmental prerequisites, Dahl and Lutz's meditation mechanism taxonomies, VCE adverse-effect variables, Hadot's spiritual exercises, Ferrer's participatory pluralism, Katz and Sharf's contextualism, Buddhist upaya, and Shinran's Other Power. The remaining contribution is a promising operational synthesis with testable predictions, not a discovered law of spiritual paths.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.json:140:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say this is standard upaya, religious coping, contemplative-development theory, spiritual bypassing caution, cultural-linguistic theology, or ordinary lineage pedagogy. They also say the ledger does not change teaching choices or predict failures better than existing teacher judgment.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.json:152:      "Soto Zen teachers familiar with Dogen's practice-realization",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.json:153:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers who give or study pointing-out instructions",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.json:164:    "risk_of_overread": "High. The ledger may turn tradition-specific soteriology into analyst-owned cells. Pure Land entrusting, Dogen practice-realization, and Dzogchen recognition may not be practitioner capacities at all, even when they have observable preconditions.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.json:165:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The audit searched Pargament, Engler, Hadot, Ferrer, Katz, Sharf, Dahl, Lutz, Davidson, Lindahl, Britton, upaya literature, Tannisho, Bendowa, and SN 45.8. It did not close-read Shinran's letters, Kyogyoshinsho, Longchenpa, Wangchuk Dorje, Christian grace manuals, Sufi fana and baqa texts, or original Pali and Japanese terms. That gap blocks any candidate-discovery claim.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger-08ac38c26b5e49aa.json:175:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Pargament, Engler, Dahl, Hadot, Ferrer, Katz, Sharf, upaya theory, and Shinran, this idea claims that path requirements can be coded as a reusable vector ledger where each functional role has magnitude, direction, locus, stage, safeguards, and failure mode, and that whole-path soteriology may generate the direction of each role. Its possible contribution is predictive rubric design, not the discovery that traditions differ in agency, capacity, or context."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Dzogchen or Mahamudra luminous selfless awareness, plus Pseudo-Dionysius's claim that the divine Cause is beyond both affirmation and negation.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.json:42:      "test_surface": "Close-reading corpus of Theravada, Advaita, Christian apophatic, Dzogchen, and Mahamudra manuals.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.json:89:    "Close-read Dzogchen and Mahamudra instructions on rigpa or luminous awareness against Bahiya and Brihadaranyaka before publishing the custody model.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.json:108:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers",
