reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.json:116:      "Dogen, Bendowa, practice-realization material as presented by Everyday Zen Foundation, https://everydayzen.org/teachings/dogens-bendowa-part-2-of-3/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.json:119:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The search found strong structural neighbors in Talal Asad's discursive tradition, George Lindbeck's cultural-linguistic grammar, Robert Sharf's critique of Buddhist modernism, Ignatian discernment, and the VCE meditation-challenges literature. The audit did not close-read Japanese, Pali, Sanskrit, or Catholic primary-language sources. It also lacks interviews with solo practitioners and lineage teachers.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.json:120:    "structural_observation": "MN 22 does not leave Arittha's interpretation to private experience. The community reports the misreading, the Buddha cross-examines it, and the raft simile then teaches right use and release of the Dhamma. The method is not self-naming because wrong grasp is corrected by teacher and sangha. Bendowa strains the model. Dogen collapses practice and realization so strongly that there is no simple later event to label, yet the text still frames zazen through transmitted Buddha-dharma, trust, and instruction. The comparison supports the recognition claim, but it also shows the claim is already native to many practice ecologies rather than newly discovered."
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.json:132:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Asad, Lindbeck, Sharf, Ignatian discernment, and VCE, this idea's distinct contribution is not that communities shape religious meaning. Its possible contribution is a narrow practitioner diagnostic: after a contemplative shift, ask who could correct the interpretation, and treat the inability to name such a person as data about the experience rather than as proof or failure."
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.md:27:- Dogen, Bendowa, practice-realization material as presented by Everyday Zen Foundation, https://everydayzen.org/teachings/dogens-bendowa-part-2-of-3/
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.md:29:Structural observation: MN 22 does not leave Arittha's interpretation to private experience. The community reports the misreading, the Buddha cross-examines it, and the raft simile then teaches right use and release of the Dhamma. The method is not self-naming because wrong grasp is corrected by teacher and sangha. Bendowa strains the model. Dogen collapses practice and realization so strongly that there is no simple later event to label, yet the text still frames zazen through transmitted Buddha-dharma, trust, and instruction. The comparison supports the recognition claim, but it also shows the claim is already native to many practice ecologies rather than newly discovered.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.md:31:Secondary literature gap: The search found strong structural neighbors in Talal Asad's discursive tradition, George Lindbeck's cultural-linguistic grammar, Robert Sharf's critique of Buddhist modernism, Ignatian discernment, and the VCE meditation-challenges literature. The audit did not close-read Japanese, Pali, Sanskrit, or Catholic primary-language sources. It also lacks interviews with solo practitioners and lineage teachers.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.md:37:- "discursive tradition" "correct form and purpose" Asad practice authority
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.md:38:- "Lindbeck" "doctrine as grammar" religious experience community practice
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.md:40:- "Varieties of Contemplative Experience" appraisal teachers community progress pathology
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.md:46:- Talal Asad, The Idea of an Anthropology of Islam, Qui Parle reprint, https://bpb-ap-se2.wpmucdn.com/thinkspace.csu.edu.au/dist/c/3891/files/2020/10/Asad-Anthropology.pdf: overlap: Very close. Asad treats established practices as authorized by discursive traditions that teach correct form, purpose, performance, and correction through persons such as scholars, preachers, Sufi shaykhs, and parents.; difference: Asad is not centered on contemplative experience after a shift, and he does not propose the recognition-gap exercise for modern solo practice.; novelty impact: Major downgrade. The core claim that a practice's meaning is socially and traditionally authorized is already well established.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.md:47:- George Lindbeck, The Nature of Doctrine, summarized by Boston Collaborative Encyclopedia, https://people.bu.edu/wwildman/bce/mwt_themes_862_lindbeck.htm: overlap: Very close. Lindbeck's cultural-linguistic model says religious experience is shaped by communal symbol systems and doctrine functions like grammar for speech and conduct.; difference: Lindbeck works at the level of doctrine and religious language, not at the narrower post-practice question of whom a practitioner would let correct an interpretation.; novelty impact: Major downgrade. The idea is largely an applied version of doctrine-as-grammar.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.md:48:- Lindahl, Fisher, Cooper, Rosen, and Britton, The Varieties of Contemplative Experience, PLOS One, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239: overlap: Extremely close. VCE explicitly separates experience reports from interpretations, causal attributions, remedies, teacher guidance, and social appraisal. It notes that progress versus pathology can differ by tradition, lineage, or teacher.; difference: VCE is empirical and safety-oriented. The Lumenary idea turns the same structure into a plain teaching and low-risk reflection practice for recognition gaps.; novelty impact: This is the closest near-neighbor. It lowers the status to extended unless the new practice shows measurable benefit beyond existing teacher, clinician, or peer appraisal advice.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.md:54:Unlike Asad, Lindbeck, Sharf, Ignatian discernment, and VCE, this idea's distinct contribution is not that communities shape religious meaning. Its possible contribution is a narrow practitioner diagnostic: after a contemplative shift, ask who could correct the interpretation, and treat the inability to name such a person as data about the experience rather than as proof or failure.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.md:107:- Do not publish as a standalone doctrine claim until split-source tests show predictive gain beyond Asad, Lindbeck, Sharf, Ignatian discernment, and VCE.
