reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:55:- Clark and Chalmers, The Extended Mind, https://academic.oup.com/analysis/article/58/1/7/153111; Krueger, Extended Mind and Religious Cognition, https://philpapers.org/archive/KRUTEM-2.pdf; Luckett, Bridging Belief and Social Practice, https://philarchive.org/archive/LUCBBA-2v1: overlap: Very close for external, material, social, institutional, and ritual supports constituting cognition, selfhood, affect, and religious experience.; difference: The candidate applies the structure specifically to self negating paths and adds dissolution target, residue policy, and split-source causal prediction.; novelty impact: Large reduction. Much of continuity ecology is extended, scaffolded, or socially extended religious cognition in Lumenary vocabulary.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:56:- Talal Asad, The Idea of an Anthropology of Islam, https://voidnetwork.gr/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/The-Idea-of-an-Anthropology-of-Islam-by-Talal-Asad.pdf: overlap: Very close for practices being instructed through discursive traditions that connect past, future, present institutions, social conditions, moral selves, knowledge, and authority.; difference: Asad is not building a cross-tradition rubric for self negation or residue after self dissolution.; novelty impact: Large reduction for the ecology and causal-priority caution. The candidate's remaining contribution is a narrower comparative coding hypothesis.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:57:- George Lindbeck doctrine-as-grammar discussions, https://www.repository.cam.ac.uk/items/351e3c35-6838-49bc-9b33-3ae66dd1fea5 and https://people.bu.edu/wwildman/bce/mwt_themes_862_lindbeck.htm: overlap: Close for doctrine as rules that regulate discourse, attitude, action, communal continuity, and the shaping of life.; difference: The candidate uses grammar to predict support placement and failure modes in self negating practice rather than to explain doctrine generally.; novelty impact: Moderate to large reduction. Residue policy and continuity placement look like a specialized rule-theory application.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:58:- Lindahl et al., Varieties of Contemplative Experience, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239: overlap: Close for coding practitioner, practice, relationship, worldview, teacher, community, health, appraisal, and remedy factors in contemplative difficulty.; difference: VCE does not propose that dissolution target and residue policy predict where transformability is preserved.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction. VCE is a strong empirical baseline the candidate must outperform.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:59:- Pargament religious coping styles and Brief RCOPE, https://www.mdpi.com/2077-1444/2/1/51: overlap: Close for distributing control across self, God, and collaborative self-God relations, and for treating religious coping as multimodal and dynamic.; difference: Pargament is about coping and control, not self-negating soteriology or authorized residue after negation.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction for the support-locus axis.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:62:- Tannisho, Dogen Bendowa, and Longchen Rabjam Trekcho primary materials, https://www.themathesontrust.org/papers/fareasternreligions/Tannisho-Unno.pdf; https://buddhismnow.com/2023/10/08/practice-within-realisation-dogen/; https://www.lotsawahouse.org/tibetan-masters/longchen-rabjam/lama-yangtik-trekcho-instruction: overlap: Very close primary evidence for theologically relocated support, no-boundary practice-realization, guru reliance, vows, solitude, and post-recognition training.; difference: The candidate names these as variables in one cross-tradition model.; novelty impact: Large reduction. Several allegedly new variables are already visible in the source texts.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:67:Unlike extended mind religious cognition, Asad's discursive tradition, Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar, VCE, Pargament, Buddhist continuity-without-self literature, and prior Lumenary ledgers, this idea says that self-negating paths preserve transformability through a codable continuity ecology and predicts that dissolution target plus residue policy will partly forecast where continuity is stored after institutional, ritual, and historical controls.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:71:Candidate: Dogen's practice-realization and inherited-practice cases.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:73:Why it strains the model: Dogen's Bendowa denies a clean boundary in realization and denies a beginning in practice. Inherited religious participation can also preserve continuity before any explicit self-negating doctrine is consciously adopted. In both cases, the model may impose a migration story where the tradition presents no transfer, no threshold, or no separate continuity problem.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:79:- If: Dissolution target and residue policy exert independent pressure on continuity placement. Then: Coders who see only doctrinal negation passages can predict above baseline whether later manuals locate support in effort, attention, teacher, vow, grace, ritual, community, text, or no-boundary practice-realization. Weakens if: Prediction fails, or ritual form, institution type, teacher authority, socialization pattern, or historical borrowing predicts support placement better than dissolution target and residue policy. Test surface: Split-source blind coding across Theravada, Advaita, Soto Zen, Jodo Shinshu, Dzogchen or Mahamudra, Christian grace, Sufi fana and baqa, and secular mindfulness manuals.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:91:- Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with recognition, guru reliance, and post-recognition conduct
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:123:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.80 to about 0.56. The candidate is useful and testable, but the core components are already strongly anticipated by extended and socially extended religious cognition, Asad's discursive tradition, Lindbeck's grammar model, Pargament's agency styles, VCE influencing-factor coding, Buddhist continuity-without-self debates, and prior Lumenary ledgers. The remaining contribution is a consolidated comparative coding hypothesis with explicit causal-priority tests.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:131:- Compare predictive power against extended mind, Asad, Lindbeck, Pargament, VCE, upaya, conversion studies, situated learning, socialization, habitus, and prior Lumenary ledgers.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-word-travels-alone-2108b5e4c890babe.md:30:Secondary literature gap: Before raising novelty, read Lindbeck, The Nature of Doctrine, Talal Asad, The Idea of an Anthropology of Islam and Genealogies of Religion, Wittgenstein on language-games and forms of life, J. L. Austin on speech acts, MacIntyre on practices, Bourdieu on habitus, Panikkar on homeomorphic equivalence, Katz and Sharf on contextualism, McMahan on Buddhist modernism, Pargament on religious coping, spiritual bypassing research by Welwood, Cashwell, Fox, Picciotto, and Lindahl and Palitsky on VCE and worldview effects.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-word-travels-alone-2108b5e4c890babe.md:37:- Talal Asad discursive tradition correct form purpose practice authority religion
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-word-travels-alone-2108b5e4c890babe.md:38:- Lindbeck Nature of Doctrine cultural linguistic grammar religion
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-word-travels-alone-2108b5e4c890babe.md:41:- spiritual bypassing detachment surrender emptiness avoid psychological wounds
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-word-travels-alone-2108b5e4c890babe.md:42:- Lindahl Palitsky worldviews meditation challenges VCE influencing factors
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-word-travels-alone-2108b5e4c890babe.md:47:- Talal Asad on discursive tradition, summarized with source citation at https://www.scielo.org.za/scielo.php?pid=S1011-76012014000200004&script=sci_arttext: overlap: Very close. Asad already ties religious discourse to correct form and purpose of practice, history, institutions, and social conditions.; difference: The candidate adds modern psychological and digital-comparison misuse as a receiver-side field.; novelty impact: Downgrade to extended. The authority and practice side is established prior art.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-word-travels-alone-2108b5e4c890babe.md:51:- Lindahl et al., Varieties of Contemplative Experience, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239, and Palitsky, Lindahl et al. on worldviews, https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/10.1177/13634615221128679: overlap: Close. VCE shows similar experiences can be interpreted and managed differently by practitioner factors, practice factors, relationships, health behaviors, and worldviews.; difference: The candidate applies contextual-risk logic to individual borrowed terms rather than meditation experiences generally.; novelty impact: Keeps the model empirical-adjacent but lowers novelty.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-word-travels-alone-2108b5e4c890babe.md:56:Unlike Wittgenstein, Asad, Lindbeck, speech-act theory, spiritual bypassing, and VCE context research, this candidate says a borrowed spiritual term must pass a two-sided gate: source role plus receiver-wound misuse. That combination is useful for Lumenary practice design, but most parts are known.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-word-travels-alone-2108b5e4c890babe.md:80:- clinicians familiar with spiritual bypassing and meditation-related difficulties
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-word-travels-alone-2108b5e4c890babe.md:90:Answers that reduce originality: Practitioners say this is simply spiritual bypassing, language-games, Asad, Lindbeck, or ordinary pastoral discernment, and that the added worksheet gives no better repair than existing guidance.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-word-travels-alone-2108b5e4c890babe.md:110:Novelty adjustment: Lower novelty from 0.62 to 0.39. The core insight is strongly anticipated by Wittgenstein, Asad, Lindbeck, speech-act theory, Panikkar, spiritual bypassing, Pargament, and VCE context research. The useful Lumenary contribution is a practical two-sided gate for source role and receiver-wound misuse before public teaching. Human-condition fit is stronger than novelty: the target is stable supported readers facing loneliness, digital comparison, withdrawal, meaning loss, and achievement-contingent self-worth. It is not fit for acute crisis, unsafe relationships, psychosis, mania, severe depression, dissociation, addiction withdrawal, OCD or scrupulosity loops, or medical blackout concerns.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-word-travels-alone-2108b5e4c890babe.md:117:- Compare the model against spiritual bypassing, Pargament religious coping, VCE contextual factors, Asad discursive tradition, Lindbeck grammar, and ordinary values-based action planning.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-a-test-is-not-a-home-84a684343a09d2ca.md:26:- William James, The Varieties of Religious Experience, https://www.gutenberg.org/files/621/621-h/621-h.html, read against Ignatius of Loyola, Spiritual Exercises discernment rules, https://www.ignatianspirituality.com/making-good-decisions/discernment-of-spirits/rules-for-discernment/ and Dogen, Genjokoan, https://www.thezensite.com/ZenTeachings/Dogen_Teachings/GenjoKoan_Aitken.htm
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-a-test-is-not-a-home-84a684343a09d2ca.md:28:Structural observation: Chandogya authorizes identity with subtle essence and Atman, while SN 22.59 refuses ownership and self-identification for all aggregates, including consciousness. That supports a strict doctrine gate. James already shifts religious judgment toward fruits, Ignatian discernment tests movements by effects, timing, desolation safeguards, and disclosure to a competent spiritual person, and Dogen resists certifying realization apart from enacted practice. These primary sources strongly anticipate contact, conduct, and correction as tests of lived use.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-a-test-is-not-a-home-84a684343a09d2ca.md:30:Secondary literature gap: Before any publication, read spiritual-direction ethics, pastoral counseling, Buddhist teacher-student guidance, comparative theology, Bucar on religious appropriation, Wuthnow on seeking versus practice-oriented spirituality, Turkle on mediated conversation, Pargament on religious coping, spiritual bypassing literature, social prescribing evidence, and OCD checking and reassurance research directly. The candidate is too close to prior Lumenary records to stand without a blind distinct-content test.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-a-test-is-not-a-home-84a684343a09d2ca.md:38:- comparative method religion provenance translation strain Smith Freiberger Panikkar Lindbeck Asad
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-a-test-is-not-a-home-84a684343a09d2ca.md:39:- spiritual bypassing borrowed spiritual language avoidance unresolved grief responsibility
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-a-test-is-not-a-home-84a684343a09d2ca.md:51:- Dogen, Genjokoan, https://www.thezensite.com/ZenTeachings/Dogen_Teachings/GenjoKoan_Aitken.htm: overlap: Close on enacted verification and resistance to treating realization as a possession certified before practice.; difference: Dogen is not giving a general rule for cross-tradition borrowing by eclectic seekers.; novelty impact: Supports the analogy but lowers novelty of action-before-identity logic.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-a-test-is-not-a-home-84a684343a09d2ca.md:52:- Talal Asad, Genealogies of Religion, publisher page https://press.jhu.edu/books/title/1644/genealogies-religion, and George Lindbeck doctrine-as-grammar overview example https://www.kci.go.kr/kciportal/ci/sereArticleSearch/ciSereArtiView.kci?sereArticleSearchBean.artiId=ART001871058: overlap: Close on tradition, communal grammar, discipline, authority, and the danger of abstracting religious language from embodied practice.; difference: The candidate converts this into a low-risk seeker routing protocol.; novelty impact: The theory is old; applied synthesis is modest.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-a-test-is-not-a-home-84a684343a09d2ca.md:58:Unlike Smith, Freiberger, Panikkar, James, Ignatius, Dogen, Lindbeck, Asad, Wuthnow, Turkle, spiritual-bypassing literature, social prescribing, OCD reassurance research, and recent Lumenary contact-before-claim records, this candidate's only distinct claim is that a valid doctrine-protection test should not be handed to a lonely person as medicine unless it demonstrably increases safe contact, conduct, correction, and belonging.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-a-test-is-not-a-home-84a684343a09d2ca.md:116:Novelty adjustment: Lower novelty from 0.44 to 0.32. The local prior Contact Before Claim already contains the same two-track routing rule. External prior art strongly covers disciplined comparison, fruits-testing, discernment, action-before-identity, traditioned grammar, social connection, spiritual bypassing, and anti-checking. Keep only as a safety-focused restatement unless blind distinct-content testing shows separability.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:26:- Dogen, Bendowa, Tanahashi translation excerpt and commentary, https://everydayzen.org/teachings/dogens-bendowa-part-1-of-3/
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:28:Structural observation: SN 45.8 presents path factors as trainable functions, including right view, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. Dogen's Bendowa makes zazen not merely one transferable technique but the expression of the Way itself, where practice and realization are not cleanly separated. The pair supports the candidate's distinction between repeated operation and practice grammar. Similar sitting or effort can have different meaning, authority, and endpoint structures.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:30:Secondary literature gap: The search found strong near-neighbors in transfer-of-training theory, Barnett and Ceci's far-transfer taxonomy, Hadot on school-shaped spiritual exercises, Katz on tradition-conditioned experience, Lindbeck on doctrine as grammar, Pargament on agency allocation, situated learning, Buddhist upaya, and VCE adverse-effects coding. It did not yet close-read full books by Hadot, Katz, Sharf, Lindbeck, Lave and Wenger, or Pargament, and it did not code actual cross-training cases.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:41:- George Lindbeck doctrine as grammar rules discourse attitude action
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:42:- Pargament religion problem solving process three styles coping self directing deferring collaborative
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:43:- Varieties of Contemplative Experience meditation challenges practice practitioner relationship context
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:45:- Dogen Bendowa practice realization zazen primary text
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:54:- George Lindbeck's cultural-linguistic doctrine-as-grammar model, discussed in https://repository.up.ac.za/bitstream/handle/2263/64227/Kim_Study_2018.pdf: overlap: Close for doctrine functioning as communal rules of discourse, attitude, and action.; difference: The candidate applies grammar specifically as a rival predictor of cross-training failure before telos residue may be counted.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction for claimant-grammar conflict.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:55:- Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/: overlap: Close for agency allocation between practitioner and sacred source, especially self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles.; difference: The candidate treats agency allocation as one layer in a broader transfer-failure model rather than as the primary typology.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction, especially for claimant and support-locus claims.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:56:- Lindahl, Fisher, Cooper, Rosen and Britton, Varieties of Contemplative Experience project, https://sites.brown.edu/britton/research/the-varieties-of-contemplative-experience/: overlap: Close for qualitative coding of meditation-related difficulties, interpretations, responses, and influencing factors.; difference: The candidate predicts a narrower cause of cross-training difficulty and must beat VCE-style practice, practitioner, relationship, and context factors.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction. VCE is a strong baseline.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:62:Unlike transfer theory, Hadot, Katz, Lindbeck, Pargament, upaya, VCE, and prior Lumenary ledgers, this idea says grain is only the predictive surplus of a prior dissolution target after rehearsed operation and receiving claimant grammar have already explained what they can.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:84:- Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with direct introduction
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:124:- Compare predictive value against transfer theory, situated learning, Hadot, Katz, Sharf, Lindbeck, Pargament, upaya, VCE, and prior Lumenary ledgers.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md:30:Secondary literature gap: Read William James and Edwards on fruits and practice, Ignatian discernment and spiritual direction ethics, Alston on mystical doxastic practice and overriders, Proudfoot, Sharf, Katz, Taves, Asad, Lindbeck, VCE meditation-challenge work, Cheetah House materials, rumination and scrupulosity literature, and burnout and perfectionism literature before any public practice.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md:41:- Talal Asad discursive tradition correct practice authority orthodoxy
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md:42:- Lindahl Britton Varieties Contemplative Experience appraisal support meditation challenges
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md:52:- Lindahl et al., Varieties of Contemplative Experience, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239, and Progress or Pathology, https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/psychology/articles/10.3389/fpsyg.2020.01905/full: overlap: Close on appraisal, interpretation, social context, teacher and clinician support, and differential response to meditation-related challenges.; difference: The candidate turns safety and appraisal concerns into a simple post-blank identity-verdict delay.; novelty impact: Moderate to strong reduction, with useful safety support.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md:71:- If: Even direct-recognition traditions preserve return constraints. Then: Advaita, Dzogchen, Zen, and apophatic sources that speak strongly about immediate recognition still retain some constraint through teacher, text, lineage, vow, conduct, compassion, or ordinary functioning. Weakens if: Mature sources explicitly authorize private silence as sufficient warrant with no correction, conduct, lineage, or aftercare, and practitioners show stable integration without those constraints. Test surface: Close reading plus practitioner interviews asking for concrete misrecognition, warning, and repair cases.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md:79:- Advaita and Dzogchen teachers who teach direct recognition
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.md:27:- MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, Heart Sutra, Shinran On Jinen-Honi, and Dogen Bendowa or practice-realization sources, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html, https://www.lotsawahouse.org/words-of-the-buddha/heart-sutra, https://shinranworks.com/letters/lamp-for-the-latter-ages/on-jinen-honi-1258/, https://buddhismnow.com/2023/10/08/practice-within-realisation-dogen/
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.md:29:Structural observation: Ignatius is the closest primary-text neighbor. The director adapts exercises to the exercitant, receives reports of movements and thoughts, reveals dangerous secrecy to a confessor or spiritual person, and is also restrained from seizing the exercitant's final choice. The scruple notes already distinguish useful sensitivity from harmful over-fineness and counsel a mean. MN 22 adds that the raft must be grasped correctly before release, so release is not a generic self-check. The Heart Sutra denies attainment while retaining reliance on Prajnaparamita. Shinran and Dogen strain the whole model because no-calculation and practice-realization refuse a clean separable product that the practitioner can audit.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.md:31:Secondary literature gap: Still needs full reading of Ignatian directorial manuals, contemporary spiritual direction ethics, AA sponsorship sources, ERP and scrupulosity treatment literature, VCE person-centered support, spiritual bypassing literature, and achievement-contingent self-worth studies before practice publication.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.md:33:Risk of overread: High. External holding can be wise guidance, ordinary sponsorship, clinical triage, coercive authority, approval dependence, or OCD reassurance. No-check can mean healthy rest, avoidance, depression drift, or Dogen-style non-instrumentality. The bypasser, scorer, and oscillator labels are too crude without validated measures and concrete behavior markers.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.md:39:- Pargament religion problem solving self directing deferring collaborative coping
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.md:40:- Varieties of Contemplative Experience support structures appraisal social context meditation challenges
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.md:43:- spiritual bypassing Welwood Trungpa practice ego avoidance accountability
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.md:49:- Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, 1988, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/: overlap: Close for support locus and agency distribution: self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles already sort who is experienced as carrying problem-solving responsibility.; difference: It concerns coping with God and agency, not post-practice diagnostics, result-language checks, or self-worth scoring.; novelty impact: Reduces novelty for custody language, leaves room only for a narrower practice-safety extension.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.md:50:- Lindahl et al., The Varieties of Contemplative Experience, PLOS ONE 2017, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239: overlap: Close for meditation-related challenges, appraisal, differential support structures, and the role of social context in interpreting practice effects.; difference: VCE does not offer the exact holder-routing rule for after-use checks in high-achievement self-scorers.; novelty impact: Downgrades the safety and support parts to established contemplative-adverse-effects territory.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.md:56:Unlike Ignatian direction, Pargament agency styles, VCE support mapping, ERP anti-reassurance rules, and the prior Lumenary Who Holds The Gate record, this candidate says that a post-practice check must first ask who should hold the diagnostic today, because the same check can repair bypassing and worsen achievement-contingent self-scoring. That distinction is useful, but it is mostly a renamed and narrower safety-routing heuristic.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.md:69:- If: Practitioners using insight to avoid responsibility need a self-held return-to-conduct check more than they need rest from checking. Then: In high-bypass, low-self-scoring participants, a single conduct check increases repair behavior and reduces avoidance without increasing shame. Weakens if: The conduct check does not improve behavior, or it increases self-scoring at the same rate as in the compulsive scorer group. Test surface: Screened practice pilot with spiritual bypassing, avoidance, self-worth contingency, and next-day conduct measures.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.md:111:Novelty adjustment: Lower novelty from 0.57 to 0.28. The core is already present in the supplied Who Holds The Gate audit and has close external neighbors in Ignatian direction, spiritual direction, Pargament agency styles, contemplative adverse-effects support, ERP anti-reassurance rules, and self-focused-attention research. Human-condition fit is real but bounded: it serves stable high-achievement practitioners, founders, students, creators, caregivers, and self-directed meditators who convert insight into worth evidence. It is not for acute crisis, mania, psychosis, severe depression, dissociation, addiction withdrawal, active OCD or scrupulosity reassurance loops, abusive authority settings, or people whose main need is restored self-trust.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress-8dad9d31a3c79764.json:144:      "MN 22 raft simile, Heart Sutra no attainment, and Dogen practice-realization, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html, https://www.lotsawahouse.org/words-of-the-buddha/heart-sutra, https://buddhismnow.com/2023/10/08/practice-within-realisation-dogen/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress-8dad9d31a3c79764.json:146:    "risk_of_overread": "High. Spiritual release texts can be misused to justify quitting hard work, while Dogen can be misused to justify endless practice with no deliverable. The engine evidence is procedural, not doctrinal: it repeatedly ignored a logged audit or merge step.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-more-is-not-the-same-as-progress-8dad9d31a3c79764.json:148:    "structural_observation": "Zhuangzi and MN 22 both support release of a tool after its work is done, but they presuppose a real catch or crossing. MN 22 also stresses proper grasp before release, which prevents premature quitting. The Heart Sutra denies attainment while still relying on Prajnaparamita, so no-attainment is not simple inactivity. Dogen strains the model most, because practice and realization are inseparable, which blocks a universal before-and-after completion rule. These primary texts support a scoped after-use discipline, not the broad claim that finishing is always the next virtue."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.json:37:      "test_surface": "Screened practice pilot with spiritual bypassing, avoidance, self-worth contingency, and next-day conduct measures.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.json:52:    "Pargament religion problem solving self directing deferring collaborative coping",
