reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stop-making-silence-judge-you-426c0c34cd74415c.json:143:    "risk_of_overread": "Very high if generalized. Advaita, Dzogchen, Mahamudra, clear-light sleep, and direct-recognition lineages may treat some quiet or objectless reports as trainable evidence within strict contexts. In OCD, scrupulosity, trauma, dissociation, mania, severe depression, and unsafe authority settings, the instruction can become avoidance, checking, reassurance outsourcing, or control.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stop-making-silence-judge-you-426c0c34cd74415c.json:144:    "secondary_literature_gap": "Before publication, read Ignatian spiritual-direction ethics, VCE and Cheetah House materials, OCD and scrupulosity reassurance-seeking literature, ACT defusion and committed action, rumination stop-rule research, behavioral activation, achievement-contingent self-worth, perfectionism, spiritual bypassing, and spiritual-abuse literature. The largest empirical gap is whether no-verdict plus ordinary care beats classification-first, rest, conversation, and clinician-guided routing.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:26:- Dogen, Bendowa, especially sections 3, 4, 7, and 10, https://www.abuddhistlibrary.com/Buddhism/C%20-%20Zen/Ancestors/Dogen/Bendowa/Bendowa.htm
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:28:Structural observation: The Tannisho strongly supports the register-first move. Its decisive register is Other Power, and it names boundary failures such as self-power, calculation, doubt, wrong teacher ownership, and confusing nembutsu with the practitioner's own good act. Bendowa is the anomaly case. It names wrong understanding, false teachers, verbal clinging, and inadequate practice, but its register is practice-realization, where training and enlightenment are not two. The proposed model reads Shinran well, but its interface language strains Dogen because an interface can imply the very separation between practitioner, practice, and realization that Bendowa rejects.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:30:Secondary literature gap: The closest scholarly prior art includes Oliver Freiberger on comparison as selection, description, juxtaposition, redescription, rectification, and theory formation; Paul Hedges on comparative theology and hermeneutics; Francis Clooney's comparative theology; Katz and Sharf on contextualist and anti-experience-flattening method; Lindbeck's cultural-linguistic model; and Pargament's religious problem-solving styles. The audit did not fully close-read Clooney, Lindbeck, Dzogchen root texts, Meister Eckhart, Qushayri, Ibn Arabi, or Shinran's letters. That gap prevents any candidate-discovery claim.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:38:- Dogen Bendowa practice-realization training and enlightenment are one text
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:44:- Pargament religion problem-solving process three styles of coping
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:45:- Lindbeck Nature of Doctrine cultural linguistic model doctrine rules
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:53:- George Lindbeck, The Nature of Doctrine, cultural-linguistic model, https://openlibrary.org/works/OL5607588W/The_nature_of_doctrine: overlap: Close. Lindbeck's cultural-linguistic approach treats doctrines as rules within religious communities, which anticipates the idea that transformation claims must be read inside their own grammar.; difference: Lindbeck is a theology of doctrine and ecumenical interpretation, not a coding method for transformation registers and failure warnings across practice manuals.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction. The candidate extends a known grammar-sensitive stance into a narrower practitioner-facing tool.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:54:- Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/: overlap: Close for agency distribution. Pargament already distinguishes self-directing, deferring, and collaborative religious problem-solving styles involving different relationships between person and God.; difference: Pargament is psychological and coping-focused. The candidate uses primary-text registers of salvation, awakening, or realization and asks what vulnerabilities each tradition itself names.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction. The model must prove it predicts more than agency locus or coping style.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:56:- Dzogchen pointing-out practitioner sources, example Tergar on pointing out true nature, https://learning.tergar.org/course_library/mingyur-rinpoches-monthly-teachings/mt-august-2019-pointing-out-your-true-nature/: overlap: Close for primordial-awareness interface risks: recognition, misrecognition, teacher mediation, expectation of special experience, and the need to stabilize recognition.; difference: Dzogchen sources provide one register and its risks. The candidate compares that register with Other Power, practice-realization, divine restoration, and effortful paths without reducing them to one agency model.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction. It supports usefulness but not uniqueness.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:60:Unlike Freiberger, Clooney, Hedges, Katz, Sharf, Lindbeck, Pargament, Shinran, Dogen, and MN 22, this idea claims that comparative work should use a specific two-layer rubric: preserve the transformation register first, then code only tradition-named vulnerabilities, safeguards, and warnings against the rubric itself. Its contribution is operational and predictive, not the discovery that traditions have different registers.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:64:Candidate: Dogen's practice-realization and other no-boundary traditions where decisive transformation is not approached through a separable practitioner-event interface.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:73:- If: Direct-introduction traditions should show a warning profile distinct from Other Power traditions. Then: Dzogchen and Mahamudra materials should warn especially against misrecognition, mistaking an experience for recognition, reifying awareness, inadequate teacher relation, and failure to integrate conduct. Weakens if: Their warnings are generic morality or effort warnings, or the same profile appears regardless of claimed transformation register. Test surface: Longchenpa, pointing-out manuals, Mahamudra manuals, Tergar or other teacher-facing materials, and practitioner interviews.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:74:- If: Practice-realization traditions should resist interface grammar more than causal-cultivation or divine-gift traditions. Then: Dogen and Soto materials should correct before-after, means-end, and practitioner-event separations more often than texts framed by gradual effort, vow, grace, or recognition. Weakens if: Practice-realization texts freely use interface-like causal language without corrective pressure, or their corrections are no stronger than in unrelated traditions. Test surface: Bendowa, Genjokoan, selected Shobogenzo fascicles, Soto practice manuals, and teacher interviews.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:75:- If: A register-sensitive rubric should predict warning profiles better than direct summary or agency-locus models. Then: Independent coders should infer later manual warnings from early register statements at above-chance rates, for example calculation in Shinran, misrecognition in Dzogchen, wrong effort in gradual paths, and conceptual reification in apophatic or raft-like traditions. Weakens if: Predictions are vague, post hoc, low agreement, or no better than Pargament-style agency categories, direct textual summary, or broad tradition labels. Test surface: Inter-rater manual-coding trial across at least six traditions, with prediction scoring before coders read later warning sections.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:81:- Soto Zen teachers familiar with Dogen's practice-realization
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:82:- Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:113:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.68 to about 0.56. The register-first discipline is strongly anticipated by comparative theology, hermeneutics, contextualist mysticism scholarship, Lindbeck's cultural-linguistic model, Sharf's critique of generic experience, Pargament's agency styles, Shinran's Other Power, Dogen's practice-realization, and MN 22's self-limiting doctrine use. The remaining contribution is a useful operational extension with predictive fields, not a discovery.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:120:- Test primary texts before broad tradition labels: Tannisho chapters 1, 6, 8, 10, and 11; Shinran letters; Bendowa or Genjokoan; one Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out manual; one Christian grace or apophatic source; and one Sufi fana or baqa source.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:123:- Read Freiberger, Clooney, Hedges, Katz, Sharf, Lindbeck, Pargament, Shinran scholarship, Dogen practice-realization scholarship, upaya literature, and apophatic theology before raising novelty above extended.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:32:Secondary literature gap: The search found strong near-neighbors in Dunne on Buddhist mindfulness styles, Lutz, Jha, Dunne, and Saron on the phenomenological matrix, Lindbeck on doctrine as grammar, Foucault on technologies of the self, Hadot on spiritual exercises, Bourdieu and Wacquant on habitus and hysteresis, Pargament on religious problem-solving styles, Lave and Wenger on situated learning, Sharf and Katz on context-shaped experience, and Lindahl and Britton's VCE study. This audit did not read full monographs by Lindbeck, Asad, Hadot, Bourdieu, Katz, or Sharf, did not check Pali, Sanskrit, Tibetan, Japanese, Middle English, or Chinese terms, and did not include practitioner interviews.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:34:Risk of overread: High. The model can become too absorbent if every difference is assigned to some layer after the fact. Tannisho and radical Other Power traditions can reject the analyst's practice-direction frame. Dogen-style practice-realization can collapse means and result. Bahiya-style immediacy strains any developmental layer sequence. Community, doctrine, teacher style, clinical risk, and social belonging may explain many cases without this model.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:42:- George Lindbeck Nature of Doctrine cultural linguistic rule theory doctrine grammar
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:44:- Pargament religious problem-solving styles self-directing deferring collaborative
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:45:- Lindahl Britton Varieties of Contemplative Experience influencing factors practice practitioner relationships health behaviors
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:54:- George Lindbeck, The Nature of Doctrine, Open Library record, https://openlibrary.org/works/OL5607588W/The_nature_of_doctrine: overlap: Close structural prior. Lindbeck's cultural-linguistic and rule-theory model treats doctrine as grammar internalized through practice and training, shaping religious experience and judgment.; difference: Lindbeck is mainly theological and doctrinal, not a micro-phenomenological or adverse-practice transfer model.; novelty impact: High reduction for the claim that religious direction functions as grammar rather than mere belief.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:58:- Lindahl, Fisher, Cooper, Rosen, and Britton, Varieties of Contemplative Experience, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239: overlap: Close methodological prior. VCE codes meditation-related challenges across phenomenology, interpretations, practice factors, practitioner factors, relationships, and health behaviors.; difference: VCE does not claim that direction layers from manuals predict mismatch or repair patterns.; novelty impact: High methodological reduction. Layered direction must outperform VCE-style factor coding.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:59:- Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/: overlap: Moderate to close. Self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles already code where agency and divine support are located.; difference: Pargament studies religious coping and problem-solving, not fine-grained contemplative instruction layers or cross-tradition transfer.; novelty impact: Moderate to high reduction for custody, support locus, and claimant distribution.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:65:Unlike Dunne, Lutz, Lindbeck, Foucault, Hadot, Bourdieu, Pargament, VCE, Sharf, Katz, and prior Lumenary ledgers, the surviving distinct claim is a split-source predictive rule: code where practice direction enters before reading outcomes, then test whether layer mismatch predicts warnings, repairs, transfer resistance, and adverse effects better than technique, tradition label, social ecology, teacher style, and clinical risk. The general idea that practice has layered direction is not original.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:69:Candidate: Bahiya's immediate release, Tannisho's non-practice Other Power, and Dogen's practice-realization collapse the model's tendency to locate direction in analyzable layers.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:71:Why it strains the model: Bahiya receives a brief instruction and is said to be released immediately, so textual coding cannot show whether direction came from prior training, readiness, teacher authority, or the instruction itself. Tannisho denies self-owned practice calculation and assigns decisive efficacy to Other Power, so calling nembutsu a directed practice can distort the source. Dogen-style practice-realization refuses a clean sequence of practice first and result later, so layer location may be an analyst imposition.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:77:- If: If direction layers have real explanatory force, split-source blind coders should infer warning and repair profiles from entry or instruction texts before reading manuals or interviews. Then: Layer scores should predict held-out warnings and repairs above baselines using tradition name, technique family, teacher style, social ecology, Pargament agency style, Lutz matrix dimensions, and VCE factors. Weakens if: Low inter-rater reliability, no predictive lift, or equally strong predictions from simpler baselines would weaken the model. Test surface: Six-case corpus: MN 10, Vivekachudamani, Tannisho, Bendowa or Genjokoan, a Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out manual, and The Cloud of Unknowing.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:88:- Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:124:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.78 to about 0.42. The useful contribution is not the broad claim that practices carry direction through many layers. That is strongly anticipated by primary texts, Dunne, Lutz, Lindbeck, Foucault, Hadot, Bourdieu, Pargament, VCE, situated learning, Sharf, Katz, and prior Lumenary ledgers. The surviving extension is the pre-registered split-source test: code where direction enters, then predict warnings, repairs, transfer resistance, and adverse effects.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:133:- Compare predictive value against Dunne mindfulness styles, Lutz phenomenological matrix, Lindbeck grammar, Pargament agency styles, habitus and hysteresis, situated learning, VCE factors, teacher style, social ecology, intensity, and clinical-risk baselines.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice-e59e1c607fa2dc18.md:136:- Use Bahiya, Tannisho, Dogen practice-realization, inherited religion, direct introduction, and successful dual practice as anomaly classes rather than confirming examples.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stratified-post-negation-authorization-940b94daf10fd12f.md:31:Secondary literature gap: Before raising novelty, compare directly with Steven Katz on contextualist mystical experience, Robert Sharf on experience as rhetorically and institutionally authorized, George Lindbeck on doctrine as grammar, Talal Asad on discursive tradition, Madhyamaka non-positioning, Advaita work on svaprakasha and adhyasa, and contemplative-science papers that separate levels of explanation in neuroscience translation. Also compare with internal Lumenary records: Residual Burden of Proof After Negation, The Inferential Gap, The Brain Model Already Took a Side, and You Cannot Prove the One Who Is Asking.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stratified-post-negation-authorization-940b94daf10fd12f.md:39:- George Lindbeck doctrine as grammar religious language practice interpretation
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stratified-post-negation-authorization-940b94daf10fd12f.md:40:- Talal Asad discursive tradition authorized practice anthropology religion
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stratified-post-negation-authorization-940b94daf10fd12f.md:44:- Varieties of Contemplative Experience interpretation support meditation adverse effects identity distress
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stratified-post-negation-authorization-940b94daf10fd12f.md:51:- George A. Lindbeck, The Nature of Doctrine, doctrine-as-grammar model: overlap: Close on treating doctrinal language as rule-governed grammar that authorizes what can be said, denied, or practiced inside a tradition.; difference: Lindbeck is not focused on post-negation contemplative states, and does not supply the candidate's stratum-specific post-state safety test.; novelty impact: Moderate to strong reduction. The grammatical-authorizing structure is old.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stratified-post-negation-authorization-940b94daf10fd12f.md:52:- Talal Asad, The Idea of an Anthropology of Islam, discursive tradition, https://web.stanford.edu/class/educ356/Readings/Asad_The_Idea_of_an_Anthropology_of_Islam.pdf: overlap: Close on practices being authorized, argued over, and corrected through traditions, texts, authorities, and embodied disciplines rather than free-standing experience.; difference: Asad is an anthropology of tradition, not a post-negation contemplative codebook. The candidate adds objectless-state and de-identification scope.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction. The authority-stratum discipline is known, though the narrow target is more specific.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stratified-post-negation-authorization-940b94daf10fd12f.md:55:- Lindahl et al., Varieties of Contemplative Experience, PLOS ONE 2017, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239: overlap: Close on meditation-related interpretation, distress, support context, and the need to distinguish phenomenology, meaning-making, and remedies.; difference: VCE is broader and descriptive. The candidate creates a post-negation authorization rubric and ties it to identity-verdict risk.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction for human-condition and safety framing, but the exact comparative rubric remains an extension.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stratified-post-negation-authorization-940b94daf10fd12f.md:59:Unlike Katz, Sharf, Lindbeck, Asad, Madhyamaka non-positioning, Advaita self-luminosity debates, VCE support routing, and prior Lumenary inference-policy records, this candidate says post-negation counsel and comparison should be coded by the same three controls: authorization mode, source stratum, and observed practitioner effect. That is a useful synthesis and protocol refinement, not a standalone discovery yet.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stratified-post-negation-authorization-940b94daf10fd12f.md:65:Why it strains the model: If a text or practice intentionally collapses the distinction between denial, refusal, and recognition, the authorization-mode grid may impose categories the source rejects. Dogen practice-realization, Dzogchen pointing-out, Mahamudra direct introduction, and some Madhyamaka sources may make authorization inseparable from performance and relation, not a codeable stance after an event.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stratified-post-negation-authorization-940b94daf10fd12f.md:71:- If: Post-negation authorization mode is a real comparative variable rather than a relabeling of tradition identity. Then: Blind coders using source-stratum passages can predict held-out warnings, repair instructions, or teacher counsel better than coders using tradition label, generic doctrine, or neuroscience mechanism alone. Weakens if: Inter-rater agreement is poor, all major passages require multiple equally plausible modes, or tradition label predicts warnings and repairs as well as the authorization rubric. Test surface: Split-source coding study across Brihadaranyaka, Shankara, SN 22.59, SN 22.95, Udana 1.10, MMK 18.6, Dogen, Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out manuals, and contemporary mindfulness adverse-event guidance.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stratified-post-negation-authorization-940b94daf10fd12f.md:82:- Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with direct introduction
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stratified-post-negation-authorization-940b94daf10fd12f.md:124:- Compare predictive value against Katz contextualism, Sharf, Lindbeck, Asad, Madhyamaka scholarship, Advaita svaprakasha studies, VCE, Cheetah House materials, Pargament agency styles, and prior Lumenary correction-holder models.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "The candidate assumes a distinguishable beginning where some holder takes custody before the practitioner can authorize the path. Dogen-style practice-realization weakens the before-after sequence because practice and realization are not two separate states. Inherited religion can make beginning indistinguishable from ordinary socialization. Successful dual practice can show multiple support systems coexisting without a single contested custody arrangement."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:31:      "test_surface": "Split-source blind coding across Orange, Tannisho or Ofumi, Benedictine novitiate texts, OCIA, SN 55.5 and related Theravada manuals, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra entry source, and one Sufi or Islamic initiation source.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:60:    "Lindbeck doctrine as grammar religion practice training participation",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:61:    "Pargament religion problem-solving self-directing deferring collaborative agency",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:99:      "difference": "Lindbeck's grammar model is broader and not specifically about beginnings, custody holders, or predictive testing of warnings and repairs.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:102:      "source": "George Lindbeck, doctrine-as-grammar and cultural-linguistic religion, summarized at https://www.saet.ac.uk/Christianity/TheologicalLanguage and https://people.bu.edu/wwildman/bce/mwt_themes_862_lindbeck.htm"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:105:      "difference": "Pargament studies coping and problem solving, not initiation or the first authorization of transformative practice under grace, vow, teacher, rule, ritual, or community custody.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:108:      "source": "Kenneth Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:141:    "Run matched comparisons where social ecology can be partially controlled, especially Jodo Shinshu versus Jodo Shu, Augustinian grace traditions versus synergist neighbors, Benedictine novitiate versus less formal lay formation, OCIA versus inherited Catholic formation, and Dzogchen pointing-out versus gradual Tibetan path training.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:142:    "Compare predictive value against Rambo conversion stages, Lofland-Stark conversion conditions, Van Gennep and Turner liminality, Lindbeck doctrine-as-grammar, Lave and Wenger legitimate peripheral participation, Kupari and Utriainen ritual-learning data, Pargament agency styles, catechumenate scholarship, monastic formation scholarship, upaya pedagogy, VCE factor coding, and prior Lumenary ledgers.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:143:    "Treat Dogen practice-realization, inherited religion, successful dual practice, and traditions that reject agency accounting as anomaly classes rather than confirming examples.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:147:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.76 to about 0.43. The candidate is generative, but most of its structure is already present in local Lumenary records, especially Entry-State Ledger, Threshold Grammar Under Translation Strain, Compound Entry Grammar, Layered Authorization of Beginning, and Operational Remainder Ecology. External near-neighbors further reduce the claim: Rambo covers conversion process, Lave and Wenger cover pre-mastery participation, Kupari and Utriainen apply that to religious newcomers, Lindbeck covers doctrine as grammar, Pargament covers agency distribution, Orange and Shinran give near-exact prescriptive beginning cases, Benedict and OCIA give institutional formation cases. The remaining contribution is a sharper label for prescriptive versus retrospective custody, not a discovery-level idea.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:167:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with direct introduction",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:180:    "secondary_literature_gap": "Search and close-reading covered accessible primary texts, local prior Lumenary records, conversion theory, legitimate peripheral participation, doctrine-as-grammar, catechumenate sources, religious coping, ritual learning, and contemplative adverse-experience methodology. It did not fully review Rambo's full monograph, Lindbeck's The Nature of Doctrine, Talal Asad in full, Van Gennep and Turner in full, Japanese Pure Land scholarship, Dogen scholarship, Tibetan pointing-out manuals, Islamic bayah and Sufi tarbiya sources, Sanskrit guru-disciple materials, original-language sources, or practitioner interviews.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.json:190:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike prior Lumenary entry ledgers, Rambo conversion theory, legitimate peripheral participation, Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar, Pargament's agency styles, Orange, Shinran, Benedict, and OCIA, this candidate's only distinct claim is that beginnings should be coded as custody of unstable attention, trust, agency, and interpretation, and that entry doctrine should be classified as either retrospective narration or prescriptive control. That difference is useful but thin, because prior Lumenary records and older sources already contain most of the structure."
