reviews/originality/2026-05-29-keep-what-can-correct-you-8144312cebdf1b38.json:146:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike MN 22, Ignatian discernment, VCE, James, Asad, Lindbeck, Sells, and the prior Lumenary recognition-gap audit, this idea's possible contribution is a narrow safety heuristic: after method release, verify that some trustworthy correction path remains, and test whether naming that path reduces inflation, shame, and isolated overinterpretation without increasing dependency."
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-must-fit-the-wound-6c82ef9b2db9c563.md:25:- MN 2 and MN 22, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN2.html and https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html, read against Huangbo, On the Transmission of Mind, https://gutenberg.org/ebooks/25236
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-must-fit-the-wound-6c82ef9b2db9c563.md:26:- SN 22.59, Dogen Bendowa, Shinran's Other Power letter, and Upaya-kaushalya, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html, https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf, https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/, https://encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Upaya-kaushalya
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-must-fit-the-wound-6c82ef9b2db9c563.md:28:Structural observation: MN 2 already supplies a question-fit gate by distinguishing appropriate from inappropriate attention and warning that self-questions generate view tangles. MN 22 supplies a right-grasp gate through the water-snake and raft similes. Huangbo strains analytic questioning by treating seeking Mind as a distortion. SN 22.59 permits disciplined aggregate investigation, while Dogen and Shinran strain self-owned result language in different ways. Upaya makes audience capacity and need central to teaching. The candidate's three gates are coherent, but each gate has strong prior art.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-must-fit-the-wound-6c82ef9b2db9c563.md:30:Secondary literature gap: Before publication, read Collingwood on question-answer presuppositions, Gadamer on priority of the question and application, Austin on felicity and misfire, Lindbeck on doctrine as grammar, Asad on discursive tradition, upaya scholarship, spiritual bypassing research, VCE and Progress or Pathology, case formulation-driven CBT, ACT, OCD and scrupulosity reassurance literature, and spiritual direction ethics.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-must-fit-the-wound-6c82ef9b2db9c563.md:42:- spiritual bypassing psychological wounds avoidance spiritual practice
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-must-fit-the-wound-6c82ef9b2db9c563.md:51:- Lindahl et al., The Varieties of Contemplative Experience, PLOS ONE 2017, and Progress or Pathology, Frontiers in Psychology 2020, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239, https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/psychology/articles/10.3389/fpsyg.2020.01905/full: overlap: Very close on support and wound fit. These studies separate phenomenology, interpretation, management, practitioner factors, practice factors, relationships, health behaviors, teacher skills or resources, functional impairment, and need for intervention.; difference: The candidate narrows those variables to the initiating question after self-negation.; novelty impact: Strong downgrade for safety and support originality. Retain only if question-fit adds prediction beyond VCE-style factors.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-must-fit-the-wound-6c82ef9b2db9c563.md:56:Unlike MN 2, MN 22, upaya, Collingwood, Gadamer, VCE, spiritual bypassing research, and prior Lumenary question-permission records, this idea claims that a self-negating question becomes teachable only when source permission, correction support, and human-wound fit are jointly satisfied and tested against outcomes.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-must-fit-the-wound-6c82ef9b2db9c563.md:68:- If: The three gates add predictive value beyond generic good judgment. Then: Blind coders can identify source-permitted question, correction holder, and non-fit wound from source and context data before seeing warnings, and those labels predict held-out repair instructions better than tradition label, support-holder-only, or VCE-factor baselines. Weakens if: Coders cannot agree, need outcome passages to infer the gates, or the model adds no prediction beyond teacher style, social ecology, clinical risk, sleep loss, or ordinary support. Test surface: Split-source inter-rater coding across SN 22.59, MN 2, MN 22, Huangbo, Bendowa, Tannisho or Shinran letters, Dzogchen direct introduction, and Rinzai koan sources.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-must-fit-the-wound-6c82ef9b2db9c563.md:76:- Soto Zen teachers and Dogen scholars
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-must-fit-the-wound-6c82ef9b2db9c563.md:79:- Dzogchen and Mahamudra teachers
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-must-fit-the-wound-6c82ef9b2db9c563.md:90:- Is this just upaya, spiritual direction, case formulation, VCE differential diagnosis, spiritual bypassing triage, or ordinary teacher judgment in new terms?
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-must-fit-the-wound-6c82ef9b2db9c563.md:113:Novelty adjustment: Lower novelty from 0.38 to 0.33. The idea is heavily anticipated by MN 2, MN 22, upaya, hermeneutics, doctrine-as-grammar, discursive-tradition analysis, spiritual bypassing literature, VCE differential diagnosis, clinical case formulation, and recent Lumenary question-permission records. Preserve as an extended three-gate consolidation only if split-source testing shows predictive gain.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:28:- Shinran, On Jinen Honi, and Dogen shusho itto summary, https://shinranworks.com/hymns-in-japanese/hymns-of-the-dharma-ages/on-jinen-honi/ and https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:30:Structural observation: Ignatius already makes gate custody explicit. The exercitant reports movements and thoughts, the director adapts exercises, and disclosure to a confessor or spiritual person breaks the secrecy of deceptive movements. Yet Annotation 15 also limits the director, the guide is not supposed to seize the final choice. Shinran strains the model from the opposite side: jinen honi rejects practicer calculation and warns that even talking about no-working can become another form of working. Dogen also strains the return-test frame because practice and realization are not separated as cause and later product. The candidate's structure is therefore not a discovery at the primary-text level. Its possible contribution is a routing rule for deciding when Ignatian-style disclosure, clinical support, fixed-rule gating, or no-result practice is appropriate.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:32:Secondary literature gap: The audit did not read full Ignatian directorial manuals, contemporary spiritual direction ethics, full Dogen Bendowa or Eihei Shingi, Shinran and Tannisho in Japanese, OCD scrupulosity treatment literature beyond abstracts, or the full measurement-based care and guided self-help literatures. It also needs direct work in perfectionism, achievement-contingent self-worth, and contemplative adverse effects before public practice guidance.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:39:- Dogen shusho itto practice realization result cause effect Bendowa
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:41:- Pargament religion problem solving process self-directing deferring collaborative coping
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:44:- spiritual bypassing Picciotto Fox Neto phenomenology psychological avoidance spiritualizing
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:45:- Varieties of Contemplative Experience meditation-related challenges teacher clinician support factors
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:55:- Lindahl, Fisher, Cooper, Rosen, and Britton, The varieties of contemplative experience, PLOS ONE 2017, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239, plus Lindahl, Britton, Cooper, and Kirmayer, Toward a Person-Centered Approach, https://bpb-us-w2.wpmucdn.com/sites.brown.edu/dist/f/330/files/2023/10/Lindahl-2019-Oxford-Handbook-of-Meditation-chapter.pdf: overlap: Close structural near-neighbor. These sources ask how experiences are appraised, which social agents shape interpretation, and what type of support a particular experience requires.; difference: They focus on meditation-related challenges and appraisal, not on return tests, non-instrumental practice scope gates, or self-scoring high achievers.; novelty impact: Downgrades the triage and support-holder parts to known contemplative-safety territory.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:56:- Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, Journal for the Scientific Study of Religion 1988, summary at https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/: overlap: Close for agency and responsibility distribution. Self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles already model who is experienced as holding problem-solving responsibility.; difference: Pargament concerns coping with God and individual agency, not diagnostic gate custody across teacher, peer, clinician, fixed rule, or no practice.; novelty impact: Reduces novelty for support-locus language but leaves room for a practice-safety routing extension.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:59:- Mor and Winquist, Self-Focused Attention and Negative Affect: A Meta-Analysis, Psychological Bulletin 2002, DOI http://dx.doi.org/10.1037/0033-2909.128.4.638, indexed at https://cris.huji.ac.il/en/publications/self-focused-attention-and-negative-affect-a-meta-analysis/: overlap: Strong support and partial near-neighbor for the risk side. Private self-focus is linked with depression and generalized anxiety, making repeated self-checks risky for ruminative users.; difference: The meta-analysis does not prescribe gate holders or distinguish spiritual bypassers from achievement scorers.; novelty impact: Supports the safety rationale but does not make the model original.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:60:- Spiritual bypassing literature, for example Picciotto, Fox, and Neto, A phenomenology of spiritual bypass, Journal of Spirituality in Mental Health 2018, indexed at https://openurl.ebsco.com/fulltext/gcd%3A132497915, and Fox and Picciotto, https://brill.com/view/journals/cvj/64/2/article-p227_7.xml: overlap: Close for the bypasser category: spiritual ideas or practices can defend against difficult emotion, psychological work, responsibility, and ordinary conduct.; difference: The literature does not combine bypass detection with non-instrumental scope gating and gate-custody assignment.; novelty impact: Downgrades the bypasser half of the model to known clinical-spiritual territory.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:65:Unlike Ignatian spiritual direction, VCE person-centered support, Pargament agency styles, routine outcome monitoring, guided self-help, spiritual bypassing literature, and prior Lumenary return and scope-gate models, this claim says a public practice instruction should pass through three ordered gates: result-language permission, current bypassing versus self-scoring risk, and custody of the diagnostic itself. Its novelty depends on whether that three-gate routing predicts harm, repair, or non-fit better than existing spiritual direction, clinical triage, and contemplative-safety frameworks.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:77:- If: Result-language permission is a real first gate rather than an analyst's imposed vocabulary. Then: Split-source coding will show that texts coded as instrumental from doctrinal or instruction passages contain more held-out return, fruit, stewardship, or conduct-test warnings, while Dogen and Shinran-style non-instrumental cases contain more form, vow, no-calculation, or practice-realization correction language. Weakens if: Coders cannot reliably distinguish instrumental from non-instrumental cases, or held-out warning and correction language does not differ after controlling for tradition, teacher style, and institution. Test surface: Blind coding of Ignatius, MN 22, Dogen Bendowa or Genjokoan, Shinran and Tannisho, Rinzai koan training, apophatic Christian texts, Sufi fana and baqa sources, and modern practice manuals.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:86:- Soto Zen teachers and Dogen scholars
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:121:Novelty adjustment: Lower novelty from 0.62 to 0.42. The gate-holder idea is already close to Ignatian discernment, spiritual direction, contemplative adverse-effects support, routine outcome monitoring, guided self-help, Pargament agency styles, and OCD reassurance literature. The surviving contribution is narrower: a Lumenary safety-routing heuristic that combines result-language permission, current bypassing or scoring state, and diagnostic custody. Human-condition fit is real but bounded. It is for functioning high achievers, founders, students, creators, professionals, and spiritual practitioners who either use insight to avoid conduct or convert practice into proof of worth. It is not for acute crisis, mania, psychosis, severe depression, dissociation, trauma activation, addiction withdrawal, coercive workloads, active OCD or scrupulosity reassurance loops, abusive communities, or people without trustworthy support.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md:130:- Read full sources before public use: Ignatian directorial literature, contemporary spiritual direction ethics, VCE and Cheetah House materials, Pargament, measurement-based care, guided self-help, rumination and self-focused attention, achievement-contingent self-worth, perfectionism, spiritual bypassing, and scrupulosity ERP.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Successful dual-trained or hybrid practitioners who switch methods smoothly after clear instruction, plus traditions that refuse the analyst's developmental sequence, especially Soto practice-realization, Dzogchen direct introduction, Pure Land Other Power, inherited practice, and apophatic silence.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.json:33:      "test_surface": "Pre-registered corpus coding across MN 10, SN 22.59, Vivekachudamani, Brihadaranyaka, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra manual, one Soto source, one Pure Land source, one Sufi source, and one Christian apophatic source.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.json:71:    "\"Lindahl\" \"Britton\" Varieties of Contemplative Experience practice factors interpretation",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.json:134:      "source": "Lindahl, Fisher, Cooper, Rosen, and Britton, The Varieties of Contemplative Experience, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.json:157:    "Compare predictive value against habitus and hysteresis, technologies of the self, spiritual exercises, pious habitus, Asad and Lindbeck, Katz and Sharf, Dunne styles, Lutz phenomenological matrix, VCE factors, social ecology, teacher style, intensity, and clinical-risk baselines.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.json:179:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.json:196:    "risk_of_overread": "High. The model risks treating texts, teacher norms, report vocabulary, actual phenomenology, and embodied habit as one process. It also risks making every difference count as grain and every doctrinal sentence count as residue policy. Traditions such as Soto practice-realization, Dzogchen direct introduction, Pure Land Other Power, inherited practice, and apophatic silence may reject the developmental sequence or the analyst's residue vocabulary.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.json:197:    "secondary_literature_gap": "Search found close near-neighbors in Foucault on technologies of the self, Hadot on spiritual exercises, Bourdieu and Wacquant on habitus and hysteresis, Saba Mahmood on pious habitus, Lutz, Dunne, Jha, and Saron on the phenomenological matrix, Dunne on Buddhist mindfulness styles, Lindahl and Britton's VCE work, Katz and Sharf on constructed or rhetorically framed experience, and Luhrmann on attentional learning. This audit did not review full books by Foucault, Hadot, Bourdieu, Mahmood, Asad, Lindbeck, or Katz, nor original-language Pali, Sanskrit, Tibetan, Japanese, Arabic, or Persian sources, nor actual practitioner interviews.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.json:207:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Foucault, Hadot, Bourdieu, Wacquant, Mahmood, Lutz, Dunne, Saron, Lindahl, Britton, Katz, Sharf, Luhrmann, and prior Lumenary Grain and Residue records, this idea's distinct claim is a testable temporal bridge: residue authorization is not only a doctrinal policy or report norm, it may become embodied grain through repeated practice, while procedural direction can install grain earlier. The difference is useful, but thin unless longitudinal and split-source tests show predictive lift beyond habitus, practice-style, report-vocabulary, and VCE-style factor baselines."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:30:      "expected_observation": "Split-source coding will show that texts coded as instrumental from doctrinal or instruction passages contain more held-out return, fruit, stewardship, or conduct-test warnings, while Dogen and Shinran-style non-instrumental cases contain more form, vow, no-calculation, or practice-realization correction language.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:32:      "test_surface": "Blind coding of Ignatius, MN 22, Dogen Bendowa or Genjokoan, Shinran and Tannisho, Rinzai koan training, apophatic Christian texts, Sufi fana and baqa sources, and modern practice manuals.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:58:    "Dogen shusho itto practice realization result cause effect Bendowa",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:60:    "Pargament religion problem solving process self-directing deferring collaborative coping",
