reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:64:    "Varieties of Contemplative Experience meditation-related challenges teacher clinician support factors",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:87:      "source": "Lindahl, Fisher, Cooper, Rosen, and Britton, The varieties of contemplative experience, PLOS ONE 2017, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239, plus Lindahl, Britton, Cooper, and Kirmayer, Toward a Person-Centered Approach, https://bpb-us-w2.wpmucdn.com/sites.brown.edu/dist/f/330/files/2023/10/Lindahl-2019-Oxford-Handbook-of-Meditation-chapter.pdf"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:90:      "difference": "Pargament concerns coping with God and individual agency, not diagnostic gate custody across teacher, peer, clinician, fixed rule, or no practice.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:93:      "source": "Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, Journal for the Scientific Study of Religion 1988, summary at https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:108:      "difference": "The meta-analysis does not prescribe gate holders or distinguish spiritual bypassers from achievement scorers.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:117:      "source": "Spiritual bypassing literature, for example Picciotto, Fox, and Neto, A phenomenology of spiritual bypass, Journal of Spirituality in Mental Health 2018, indexed at https://openurl.ebsco.com/fulltext/gcd%3A132497915, and Fox and Picciotto, https://brill.com/view/journals/cvj/64/2/article-p227_7.xml"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:132:    "Read full sources before public use: Ignatian directorial literature, contemporary spiritual direction ethics, VCE and Cheetah House materials, Pargament, measurement-based care, guided self-help, rumination and self-focused attention, achievement-contingent self-worth, perfectionism, spiritual bypassing, and scrupulosity ERP.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:137:  "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.62 to 0.42. The gate-holder idea is already close to Ignatian discernment, spiritual direction, contemplative adverse-effects support, routine outcome monitoring, guided self-help, Pargament agency styles, and OCD reassurance literature. The surviving contribution is narrower: a Lumenary safety-routing heuristic that combines result-language permission, current bypassing or scoring state, and diagnostic custody. Human-condition fit is real but bounded. It is for functioning high achievers, founders, students, creators, professionals, and spiritual practitioners who either use insight to avoid conduct or convert practice into proof of worth. It is not for acute crisis, mania, psychosis, severe depression, dissociation, trauma activation, addiction withdrawal, coercive workloads, active OCD or scrupulosity reassurance loops, abusive communities, or people without trustworthy support.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:151:      "Soto Zen teachers and Dogen scholars",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:163:      "Shinran, On Jinen Honi, and Dogen shusho itto summary, https://shinranworks.com/hymns-in-japanese/hymns-of-the-dharma-ages/on-jinen-honi/ and https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:166:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The audit did not read full Ignatian directorial manuals, contemporary spiritual direction ethics, full Dogen Bendowa or Eihei Shingi, Shinran and Tannisho in Japanese, OCD scrupulosity treatment literature beyond abstracts, or the full measurement-based care and guided self-help literatures. It also needs direct work in perfectionism, achievement-contingent self-worth, and contemplative adverse effects before public practice guidance.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:167:    "structural_observation": "Ignatius already makes gate custody explicit. The exercitant reports movements and thoughts, the director adapts exercises, and disclosure to a confessor or spiritual person breaks the secrecy of deceptive movements. Yet Annotation 15 also limits the director, the guide is not supposed to seize the final choice. Shinran strains the model from the opposite side: jinen honi rejects practicer calculation and warns that even talking about no-working can become another form of working. Dogen also strains the return-test frame because practice and realization are not separated as cause and later product. The candidate's structure is therefore not a discovery at the primary-text level. Its possible contribution is a routing rule for deciding when Ignatian-style disclosure, clinical support, fixed-rule gating, or no-result practice is appropriate."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json:176:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Ignatian spiritual direction, VCE person-centered support, Pargament agency styles, routine outcome monitoring, guided self-help, spiritual bypassing literature, and prior Lumenary return and scope-gate models, this claim says a public practice instruction should pass through three ordered gates: result-language permission, current bypassing versus self-scoring risk, and custody of the diagnostic itself. Its novelty depends on whether that three-gate routing predicts harm, repair, or non-fit better than existing spiritual direction, clinical triage, and contemplative-safety frameworks."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.md:35:Secondary literature gap: Search found close near-neighbors in Foucault on technologies of the self, Hadot on spiritual exercises, Bourdieu and Wacquant on habitus and hysteresis, Saba Mahmood on pious habitus, Lutz, Dunne, Jha, and Saron on the phenomenological matrix, Dunne on Buddhist mindfulness styles, Lindahl and Britton's VCE work, Katz and Sharf on constructed or rhetorically framed experience, and Luhrmann on attentional learning. This audit did not review full books by Foucault, Hadot, Bourdieu, Mahmood, Asad, Lindbeck, or Katz, nor original-language Pali, Sanskrit, Tibetan, Japanese, Arabic, or Persian sources, nor actual practitioner interviews.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.md:37:Risk of overread: High. The model risks treating texts, teacher norms, report vocabulary, actual phenomenology, and embodied habit as one process. It also risks making every difference count as grain and every doctrinal sentence count as residue policy. Traditions such as Soto practice-realization, Dzogchen direct introduction, Pure Land Other Power, inherited practice, and apophatic silence may reject the developmental sequence or the analyst's residue vocabulary.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.md:48:- "Lindahl" "Britton" Varieties of Contemplative Experience practice factors interpretation
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.md:63:- Lindahl, Fisher, Cooper, Rosen, and Britton, The Varieties of Contemplative Experience, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239: overlap: Close empirical-adjacent neighbor. VCE separates phenomenology, interpretation, response, practice factors, practitioner factors, relationships, and health behaviors, and shows that similar experiences can be appraised and managed differently.; difference: VCE does not claim residue authorization becomes embodied grain or that early and mature mismatch have distinct signatures.; novelty impact: High methodological reduction. Any test must show added predictive value beyond VCE-style factor coding.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.md:69:Unlike Foucault, Hadot, Bourdieu, Wacquant, Mahmood, Lutz, Dunne, Saron, Lindahl, Britton, Katz, Sharf, Luhrmann, and prior Lumenary Grain and Residue records, this idea's distinct claim is a testable temporal bridge: residue authorization is not only a doctrinal policy or report norm, it may become embodied grain through repeated practice, while procedural direction can install grain earlier. The difference is useful, but thin unless longitudinal and split-source tests show predictive lift beyond habitus, practice-style, report-vocabulary, and VCE-style factor baselines.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.md:73:Candidate: Successful dual-trained or hybrid practitioners who switch methods smoothly after clear instruction, plus traditions that refuse the analyst's developmental sequence, especially Soto practice-realization, Dzogchen direct introduction, Pure Land Other Power, inherited practice, and apophatic silence.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.md:81:- If: Split-source coding of manuals should identify where direction first enters, then predict held-out warnings and repair instructions. Then: Procedural-direction texts should predict immediate attentional errors, such as tracking the wrong object or applying judgment when suspended. Residue-authorization texts should predict claim-confusion warnings, such as reifying awareness, collapsing into nihilism, self-crediting, or refusing responsibility. Social-report norms should predict acceptable testimony and teacher correction patterns. Weakens if: Held-out warnings are predicted as well or better by tradition identity, teacher style, institution, practice intensity, social ecology, or generic beginner problems, with no incremental value from direction-layer coding. Test surface: Pre-registered corpus coding across MN 10, SN 22.59, Vivekachudamani, Brihadaranyaka, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra manual, one Soto source, one Pure Land source, one Sufi source, and one Christian apophatic source.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.md:94:- Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.md:142:- Compare predictive value against habitus and hysteresis, technologies of the self, spiritual exercises, pious habitus, Asad and Lindbeck, Katz and Sharf, Dunne styles, Lutz phenomenological matrix, VCE factors, social ecology, teacher style, intensity, and clinical-risk baselines.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "No-search or no-before-after paths may still show predictable warnings and repairs. Huangbo, Dogen, Dzogchen, Pure Land Other Power, and Rinzai koan practice may reject the candidate's search-sequence restriction while still producing path-specific failure clusters.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.json:13:    "Search-refusing paths such as Huangbo-style no-seeking, Dogen practice-realization, and Dzogchen direct recognition should not be counted as confirmations of remainder relocation without independent predictions.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.json:36:      "test_surface": "Longitudinal interviews with practitioners switching between vipassana or self-inquiry and Huangbo-style Chan, Soto shikantaza, Dzogchen direct introduction, or Pure Land Other Power.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.json:55:    "Huangbo Transmission of Mind no seeking mind cannot seek mind",
