reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.json:58:    "Varieties of Contemplative Experience meditation challenges support structures"
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.json:77:      "source": "Clark and Chalmers, The Extended Mind, https://www.consc.net/papers/extended.html"
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.json:83:      "source": "Joel Krueger, Extended Mind and Religious Cognition, https://philarchive.org/rec/KRUTEM-2"
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.json:98:      "difference": "The candidate interprets Huangbo not as support relocated to no-seeking practice, but as a scope limit on the whole remainder model.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.json:99:      "novelty_impact": "Supports narrowing, but also risks overclaiming if Huangbo sources still predict distinctive warnings.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.json:100:      "overlap": "Primary-text anomaly. Huangbo treats seeking as the mistake, which strains any model that expects a post-negation remainder question to arise.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.json:101:      "source": "Huangbo, On the Transmission of Mind, https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/25236 and no-seeking excerpt at https://dailyzen.com/journal/mind-is-the-buddha/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.json:113:  "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.55 to 0.34. The falsifiability and degenerating-programme structure is already Popper and Lakatos. Distributed support is already extended mind, religious cognition, Asad-style tradition analysis, Lindbeck-style grammar, and VCE support-context work. Preserve as an extended internal audit-control rule only if it produces better merge, retirement, and prediction decisions than prior Lumenary gates.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.json:131:      "Chan or Zen teachers familiar with Huangbo and huatou",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.json:132:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.json:140:      "SN 22.59 and SN 22.95, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html and https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_95.html, read against Huangbo no-seeking materials, https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/25236 and https://dailyzen.com/journal/mind-is-the-buddha/",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.json:141:      "Dogen Bendowa practice-realization sources, especially https://www.sotozen.com/eng/library/stories/vol01.html and https://wwzc.org/sites/default/files/Bendowa-book.pdf, read against Clark and Chalmers, The Extended Mind, https://www.consc.net/papers/extended.html"
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.json:144:    "secondary_literature_gap": "Before publication, read Popper beyond the slogan, Lakatos on progressive versus degenerating programmes, Duhem-Quine underdetermination, Kuhn and Feyerabend on anomaly handling, Clark and Chalmers on active externalism, Krueger on extended religious cognition, Asad on discursive tradition, Lindbeck on doctrine as grammar, VCE and Progress or Pathology on support and intervention criteria, and Dogen, Huangbo, Dzogchen, and Rinzai practitioner manuals for non-search cases.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.json:145:    "structural_observation": "SN 22.59 and SN 22.95 authorize a repeated inspection of the aggregates and produce a recognizable release sequence. They fit a search-and-negation model better than Huangbo, where seeking Mind with mind is already suspect, and better than Dogen, where practice and realization are not cleanly sequenced. Clark and Chalmers make distributed support conceptually ordinary, while Krueger applies extension to religious cognition. That means merely finding support in text, ritual, body, teacher, or community is not a Lumenary discovery. The candidate's real contribution is the demand to separate distributed support as background condition from differential prediction as actual model content."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:13:    "Dogen's practice-realization refuses the separation between method, verification, and later custody.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:25:  "exact_claim": "The keep, release, embody model silently assumes that the practitioner provisionally owns the method and that there is an after in which custody of the result can be decided. Radical Other Power and practice-realization break those assumptions: in Shinran's jinen honi the practitioner never owns the method, trust, or result, while in Dogen's shusho-itto there is no discrete after outside practice. Therefore the custody model is bounded, and for depleted over-managing people the prompt to decide what to keep, release, or embody can become one more burden.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:32:      "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Coders cannot separate refusal from relocation, or retain, release, embody categories work equally well across Shinran, Dogen, Advaita, Theravada, Rinzai, apophatic Christian, and Sufi sources."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:52:    "Dogen Bendowa practice realization one shusho itto verification outside practice",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:53:    "Dogen practice and realization are one scholarship",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:55:    "Pargament deferring religious coping style agency God control",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:85:      "difference": "Pargament studies coping style and control attribution, not method-completion temporality or practitioner ownership as scope conditions.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:88:      "source": "Pargament et al., religious problem-solving styles"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:101:    "Close-read Shinran's Japanese terms around jinen honi and hakarai, Dogen on shusho-itto and non-gaining, and practitioner manuals where concrete guidance appears.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:104:  "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.55 to 0.28. The non-ownership and no-after structures are well established in Shinran and Dogen, and the core Lumenary comparison is already present in the recent audit of You cannot release what you never held. The modern caution overlaps with known rumination, perfectionism, and burnout risks. Human-condition fit is strong for depleted over-managers, caregivers, founders, professionals, students, and serious practitioners who turn even rest into performance. It is not for people who need planning, accountability, medication, therapy, social support, or material workload reduction, nor for acute crisis, addiction withdrawal, severe depression, dissociation, psychosis, mania, or responsibility avoidance.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:117:      "Soto Zen teachers and Dogen scholars",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:128:      "Dogen, Bendowa and shusho-itto practice-realization sources, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:131:    "secondary_literature_gap": "This audit did not read Japanese sources, Dogen commentarial scholarship, Jodo Shinshu scholarship, grace-effort theology, Pargament's full agency-style work, or ethnographic practitioner accounts. It also did not verify whether other traditions with inherited practice, ritual-first formation, or apophatic unsaying similarly refuse the ownership-and-after assumptions.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:132:    "structural_observation": "Shinran relocates efficacy to Other Power and warns against calculation, so the practitioner is not the owner who later decides how to carry the method. Dogen's practice-realization collapses the gap between practice and verification, so a later custody decision is not the native shape of the path. These are strong boundary cases against a universal after-use grid, but they do not eliminate all guidance: Shin still has nembutsu, warnings, and entrusting language, and Soto still has zazen, discipline, teacher correction, and conduct."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json:144:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Shinran's Other Power, Dogen's practice-realization, Pargament's agency styles, burnout rumination literature, and prior Lumenary release and custody models, this idea's possible contribution is an explicit scope test: before applying keep, release, or embody guidance, first ask whether the tradition grants provisional practitioner ownership and a discrete after, and whether the person has enough agency to benefit from a custody prompt."
observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:23:- Primary-text comparison: Dogen's Bendowa refuses a separation between cultivation and realization while still recommending direct practice, https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf. Huangbo's On the Transmission of Mind refuses seeking as a way to grasp mind, consulted via Blofeld PDF record, https://merton.bellarmine.edu/s/merton/media/51897, and Chan transmission analysis, https://www.mdpi.com/2077-1444/12/4/279. Shinran's Tannisho denies self-powered practice while preserving teacher, vow, and correction against divergence, https://jodoshinshu.faith/tannisho-a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:24:- Thinking method source: Dogen's practice-realization was used as a lens to stop assuming before, after, method, and result. Critique of that lens: it can dissolve real sequence too quickly, so it was checked against Shinran's warnings about calculation and Huangbo's sharper refusal of seeking.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:25:- Closest prior-art pressure: Clark and Chalmers, The Extended Mind, https://www.consc.net/papers/extended.html; Krueger, Extended Mind and Religious Cognition, https://philpapers.org/archive/KRUTEM-2.pdf; Talal Asad on discursive tradition, https://voidnetwork.gr/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/The-Idea-of-an-Anthropology-of-Islam-by-Talal-Asad.pdf; George Lindbeck's doctrine-as-rule near-neighbor, https://books.google.com/books/about/The_Nature_of_Doctrine.html?id=_fbYAAAAMAAJ.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:31:Huangbo may weaken the model from inside it. His search-refusal can be read as refusing not only private ownership but also every mediating support the analyst wants to name. Calling his discourse a support may domesticate a teaching meant to cut support-seeking itself. Dogen also strains the model because practice-realization may not relocate support at all; practice may simply be the expression, not a holder of continuity. A further weakness is circularity: coders may find support wherever a tradition has teachers, texts, or communities, which would make the model descriptive rather than predictive. The claim should be weakened if no-distance practitioners flourish without identifiable correction supports, or if their failures do not cluster around privatization, passivity, or performance.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:87:Survives the anomaly that Dogen, Huangbo, and Shinran each refuse a simple method-then-result timeline, yet each still preserves some form of practice, discourse, vow, teacher, or warning against distortion.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:158:- Prediction: If the distinction is real, prior art will discuss extended religious cognition, discursive tradition, doctrine as rule, spiritual exercises, and spiritual bypassing, but will not name anti-ownership support as a specific predictor of no-distance path failure. If that exact predictor already exists, novelty should fall below 0.35.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:161:- Next action: Search extended cognition, ritual studies, Pure Land studies, Dogen studies, Chan studies, Dzogchen studies, and mindfulness critique for this exact scope condition.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:171:- Next action: Code Bendowa, Uji, Huangbo, Tannisho, selected Dzogchen manuals, and practitioner reports for ownership refusal, correction holder, and named failure mode.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:196:- If this model is right, then Dogen-style, Huangbo-style, Shin-style, and Dzogchen-style texts should refuse private ownership while still protecting some concrete source of correction. If they deny both ownership and corrigible support, the model is weakened.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:199:- Compare spiritual bypassing and mindfulness optimization research with practice communities that preserve external correction. If social support predicts healthier use of no-distance language, empirical adjacency rises.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:200:- Protocol improvement: Dogen's lens should remain a warning against false sequence, not a universal solvent. Pair it with a method that preserves concrete responsibility, such as early Buddhist not-mine analysis or Shinran's warning against self-power calculation.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-first-break-problem-a1081d3f97040016.md:29:Secondary literature gap: The strongest prior art includes Plato's Meno on inquiry into what one does not know, Augustine and Orange on initium fidei, William James on volitional and self-surrender conversion, Rambo's conversion stages, Rahner's supernatural existential, Simone Kotva on effort and grace, Yogacara asraya-paravrtti, Dzogchen pointing-out literature, and transformative learning theory. The audit did not find the exact four-value cross-tradition typology with downstream predictions, but most structural ingredients are already named in adjacent literatures.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-first-break-problem-a1081d3f97040016.md:31:Risk of overread: Moderate to high. The model may project a philosophical bootstrapping problem onto practitioners who begin through family, ritual, obedience, attraction, crisis, community, or habit without experiencing a paradox. It may also collapse distinct cases: Shinran's Other Power and Orange's prevenient grace are structurally close, while Dzogchen self-disclosure and Platonic recollection may be closer than the typology admits.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-first-break-problem-a1081d3f97040016.md:43:- Dzogchen pointing out instruction recognition rigpa awareness recognizes itself
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-first-break-problem-a1081d3f97040016.md:49:- Augustine, On the Predestination of the Saints, Book I, https://www.newadvent.org/fathers/15121.htm: overlap: Near exact for the Christian version: the beginning of faith is God's gift, and even thinking with assent requires divine sufficiency.; difference: Augustine is a single-tradition theological solution, not a comparative typology across Buddhist, Pure Land, Christian, and Dzogchen cases.; novelty impact: Very high reduction for the prevenient-grace category.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-first-break-problem-a1081d3f97040016.md:60:Unlike Meno, Augustine, Orange, James, Rambo, Rahner, Kotva, Yogacara, and Dzogchen sources, this idea claims that the first-break mechanism is a cross-tradition variable that predicts later effort theory, verification, safeguards, and failure modes. That comparative-predictive use is the main contribution, not the circularity itself.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-first-break-problem-a1081d3f97040016.md:72:- If: Traditions with severe first-break solutions should show entry-point safeguards that match the feared false beginning. Then: Jodo Shinshu warns against self-power calculation, Orange-Augustinian grace traditions warn against pride and presumption, Dzogchen warns against premature recognition and fabrication, and social-encounter models warn against isolation from good friends or teachers. Weakens if: Entry warnings are no stronger or more type-specific than in mild or no-break traditions, or they track institution and polemic better than first-break mechanism. Test surface: Stage-coded analysis of entry instructions, initiation manuals, sermons, and teacher warnings.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-first-break-problem-a1081d3f97040016.md:73:- If: Anthropology should predict first-break severity. Then: Traditions with deep incapacity, sin, mappo, avidya as pervasive delusion, or ordinary mind as unreliable should use more external, prior, or self-disclosing breaks than traditions with innate goodness or workable capacities. Weakens if: Optimistic anthropologies use severe external first-break mechanisms just as often, or pessimistic anthropologies use ordinary self-cultivation without special entry safeguards. Test surface: Comparative coding of primary texts and doctrinal manuals across Confucian, Theravada, Pure Land, Christian, Dzogchen, Yogacara, and Zen sources.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-first-break-problem-a1081d3f97040016.md:83:- Dzogchen and Mahamudra teachers
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-first-break-problem-a1081d3f97040016.md:115:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.78 to about 0.62. The cross-tradition variable and downstream prediction are promising, but the first-break circularity is strongly anticipated by Meno's paradox, Augustine and Orange on the beginning of faith, James and Rambo on conversion, Rahner, Kotva, Yogacara, Dzogchen pointing-out, and transformative learning. Do not call it a discovery until the typology outperforms these prior frames in manual coding and practitioner tests.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-you-cannot-be-seeker-path-and-prize-066195ae90a18808.md:26:- SN 22.59, The Five or Anatta-lakkhana Sutta, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html, read against Dogen Bendowa practice-realization, https://www.lionsroar.com/just-wholeheartedly-sit/.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-you-cannot-be-seeker-path-and-prize-066195ae90a18808.md:28:Structural observation: Shinran relocates decisive efficacy away from the practitioner's calculation into Amida's Vow, while still preserving teacher and transmission constraints. SN 22.59 stages disciplined inspection of the aggregates and ends with release and knowledge that the task is done, but the inquiry is delivered by a teacher within a sangha, not by a lone modern self-interpreter. Dogen blocks simple separation of practice and result, but Bendowa still emphasizes master, transmission, genuine trust, and authentic teacher. The candidate's four-role grid is a plausible analytic compression, but the primary texts do not themselves state that four jobs normally exist as separable roles.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-you-cannot-be-seeker-path-and-prize-066195ae90a18808.md:30:Secondary literature gap: Before raising novelty, read Pargament et al. 1988 on self-directing, deferring, and collaborative religious coping, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/; Engler on ego development before no-self work, https://inquiringmind.com/article/0501_1_engler-interview/; Trungpa on spiritual materialism, https://chogyamtrungpa.com/quotes/using-spirituality-to-feed-egohood/; Hori on Rinzai koan curriculum, https://academic.oup.com/book/50253/chapter/422745545; VCE and Progress or Pathology, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239 and https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/psychology/articles/10.3389/fpsyg.2020.01905/full; spiritual direction ethics; attachment and secure-base literature; and prior Lumenary custody, support, question-permission, and no-management records.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-you-cannot-be-seeker-path-and-prize-066195ae90a18808.md:32:Risk of overread: High. The useful claim may be ordinary advice to have a teacher, community, sponsor, director, or therapist, restated as role distribution. Pargament already codes agency location, Engler already warns against premature no-self work, Trungpa already warns that spirituality can become ego project, and VCE already treats interpretation, community, teacher, impairment, and intervention context as outcome variables. Human-condition fit is clear but narrow: stable solo self-inquiry readers, app meditators, and eclectic practitioners with isolation, meaning loss, or achievement-contingent self-worth. It is not for acute crisis, psychosis, mania, dissociation, severe depression, addiction withdrawal, OCD or scrupulosity, trauma activation, unsafe authority, or people whose main wound is denied agency.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-you-cannot-be-seeker-path-and-prize-066195ae90a18808.md:39:- Pargament self directing deferring collaborative religious coping original religious problem solving style
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-you-cannot-be-seeker-path-and-prize-066195ae90a18808.md:43:- Varieties of Contemplative Experience meditation challenges interpretation support teacher community
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-you-cannot-be-seeker-path-and-prize-066195ae90a18808.md:48:- Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, 1988, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/.: overlap: Very close on agency placement. Self-directing, deferring, and collaborative coping already model whether the person, God, or a relation carries problem-solving.; difference: The candidate adds method-bearer, validator, and result-holder roles and applies them to post-negation contemplative pressure rather than general religious coping.; novelty impact: Strong downgrade for support and agency originality. Possible extension remains in the four-role post-negation coding.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-you-cannot-be-seeker-path-and-prize-066195ae90a18808.md:57:Unlike Pargament, Engler, Trungpa, Rinzai teacher-verification literature, VCE, and prior Lumenary custody records, this idea says post-negation distress is specifically predicted when four practice roles collapse onto one unsupported practitioner, and that externalizing even one role should reduce remainder-pressure distress.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-you-cannot-be-seeker-path-and-prize-066195ae90a18808.md:70:- If: The four roles can be reliably distinguished in texts and practice reports. Then: Blind coders can label seeker, method-bearer, validator, and result-holder from instruction passages and practitioner reports with acceptable agreement, and these labels predict warnings or repairs beyond Pargament coping style and VCE contextual factors. Weakens if: Coders cannot agree, roles collapse into tradition labels, or predictions are explained by generic teacher support, social connection, or clinical risk. Test surface: Split-source codebook on Tannisho, Shinran letters, SN 22.59, SN 45.2, Bendowa, Rinzai koan sources, and practitioner interviews.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-you-cannot-be-seeker-path-and-prize-066195ae90a18808.md:78:- Soto Zen teachers and Dogen scholars
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-you-cannot-be-seeker-path-and-prize-066195ae90a18808.md:115:Novelty adjustment: Lower novelty from 0.44 to 0.37. The broad warning is already present in Pargament, Engler, Trungpa, kalyanamitta, teacher-verification, spiritual direction, VCE, and internal Lumenary records. Retain as an extended consolidation only if the four-role grid predicts distress and repair beyond prior support-holder and agency models.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-you-cannot-be-seeker-path-and-prize-066195ae90a18808.md:122:- Run practitioner interviews for concrete failed-student and repair cases, especially Rinzai great doubt, Shinran Other Power, Theravada aggregate inquiry, Dogen practice-realization, and solo app meditation.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-one-begins-alone-3260ddf016476c06.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "No-gap traditions may still show the same support-loss failures as staged crossing paths, because Dogen, Huangbo, Dzogchen, and other no-seeking settings still rely on teachers, lineage, vows, rhythms, texts, community, and correction.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-one-begins-alone-3260ddf016476c06.json:24:  "exact_claim": "Self-release is risky when a person's steadiness has been held almost entirely by performance and control, unless some ordinary form of care already carries part of life. This support-placement claim should apply only where a path stages a real crossing; no-gap paths such as Dogen-style practice-realization and Huangbo-style no-seeking should be anomaly tests rather than extra boxes in the same table.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-one-begins-alone-3260ddf016476c06.json:34:      "expected_observation": "Dogen, Huangbo, and direct-recognition sources should warn mainly against seeking, grasping, staged attainment, and conceptualization, not against losing a carried remainder across a before-after threshold.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-one-begins-alone-3260ddf016476c06.json:36:      "test_surface": "Split-source coding of Bendowa, Genjokoan or Uji, Huangbo texts, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra direct-introduction manual, and teacher interviews.",
