reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-one-begins-alone-3260ddf016476c06.json:158:    "secondary_literature_gap": "Before any stronger claim, read Clark and Chalmers on extended mind, https://www.consc.net/papers/extended.html; Krueger on extended religious cognition; Pargament on religious coping; attachment secure-base and social baseline theory; AA Twelve Steps and sponsorship literature, https://www.aa.org/the-twelve-steps; VCE and Progress or Pathology; burnout and perfectionism sources, including WHO on burnout, https://www.who.int/standards/classifications/frequently-asked-questions/burn-out-an-occupational-phenomenon, and Curran and Hill, https://eprints.lse.ac.uk/101352/1/Curran_Hill2018.pdf; Dogen scholarship on shusho itto; Chan studies on Huangbo; Shinran scholarship on hakarai and Other Power; and internal Lumenary support-holder records.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-one-begins-alone-3260ddf016476c06.json:159:    "structural_observation": "SN 22.59 stages inquiry, disenchantment, release, and task completion, while SN 45.2 already makes good friendship central to path cultivation. That means no one begins alone is textually old in early Buddhist terms. Dogen's Bendowa makes practice and realization inseparable, yet still stresses master, transmission, trust, and authentic teacher. Huangbo's no-seeking grammar strains the crossing model, but Chan transmission literature shows that no-seeking does not mean absence of teacher, lineage, or interpretive ecology. Shinran relocates efficacy to the Vow and forbids calculation by the practicer. The support contrast is real, but the candidate's no-gap boundary may be more doctrinal than practical."
