reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-word-travels-alone-2108b5e4c890babe.json:115:  "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.62 to 0.39. The core insight is strongly anticipated by Wittgenstein, Asad, Lindbeck, speech-act theory, Panikkar, spiritual bypassing, Pargament, and VCE context research. The useful Lumenary contribution is a practical two-sided gate for source role and receiver-wound misuse before public teaching. Human-condition fit is stronger than novelty: the target is stable supported readers facing loneliness, digital comparison, withdrawal, meaning loss, and achievement-contingent self-worth. It is not fit for acute crisis, unsafe relationships, psychosis, mania, severe depression, dissociation, addiction withdrawal, OCD or scrupulosity loops, or medical blackout concerns.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-word-travels-alone-2108b5e4c890babe.json:118:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say this is simply spiritual bypassing, language-games, Asad, Lindbeck, or ordinary pastoral discernment, and that the added worksheet gives no better repair than existing guidance.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-word-travels-alone-2108b5e4c890babe.json:132:      "clinicians familiar with spiritual bypassing and meditation-related difficulties",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-word-travels-alone-2108b5e4c890babe.json:142:    "secondary_literature_gap": "Before raising novelty, read Lindbeck, The Nature of Doctrine, Talal Asad, The Idea of an Anthropology of Islam and Genealogies of Religion, Wittgenstein on language-games and forms of life, J. L. Austin on speech acts, MacIntyre on practices, Bourdieu on habitus, Panikkar on homeomorphic equivalence, Katz and Sharf on contextualism, McMahan on Buddhist modernism, Pargament on religious coping, spiritual bypassing research by Welwood, Cashwell, Fox, Picciotto, and Lindahl and Palitsky on VCE and worldview effects.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-word-travels-alone-2108b5e4c890babe.json:155:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Wittgenstein, Asad, Lindbeck, speech-act theory, spiritual bypassing, and VCE context research, this candidate says a borrowed spiritual term must pass a two-sided gate: source role plus receiver-wound misuse. That combination is useful for Lumenary practice design, but most parts are known."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Dogen's practice-realization identity and Shinran's Other Power.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "Dogen strains the premise that a road first leads to an end and then receives an after-use instruction. Shinran strains the premise that the practitioner owns the road, trust, or result enough to retain, release, or embody it. These cases may sit outside the grid's conditions of askability."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.json:12:    "Hybrid cases such as MN 22, the Heart Sutra, Rinzai koan curriculum, and Dogen's practice-realization expose the weakness of a simple confirm-or-cancel typology.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.json:30:      "test_surface": "Inter-rater coding of MN 22, Heart Sutra, Dogen Bendowa or Genjokoan, Tannisho, Rinzai koan curriculum sources, apophatic Christian texts, and Sufi fana or baqa sources.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.json:48:    "Dogen practice realization one shusho itto no verification outside practice",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.json:49:    "Pargament religious problem solving styles deferring collaborative self directing",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.json:84:      "difference": "The candidate tries to absorb this as embodied after-use, but Dogen may reject the tool-result framing altogether.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.json:85:      "novelty_impact": "Major anomaly pressure. If Dogen cannot be coded reliably, the model is only a limited checklist.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.json:97:  "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.61 to 0.31. The two-axis structure is already an internal audit instruction, and the individual components are strongly represented in MN 22, upaya, apophasis, Dogen, and therapeutic-method literature. Human-condition fit is real but narrow: achievement-driven people who convert methods and insights into worth. Non-fit cases include acute crisis, severe depression, addiction withdrawal, dissociation, psychosis, under-motivation, responsibility avoidance, and structural burnout where the primary remedy is workload or institutional change rather than reflection.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.json:110:      "Soto Zen teachers familiar with Dogen practice-realization",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.json:123:    "risk_of_overread": "High. Retained, released, and embodied may be analyst categories that flatten native distinctions. Dogen-style practice-realization, Shinran's Other Power, and no-attainment Prajnaparamita may not be hard cases inside the grid; they may reject the temporal and ownership assumptions that make the grid possible.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.json:124:    "secondary_literature_gap": "This audit did not newly inspect Pali, Sanskrit, Chinese, or Japanese originals. Before publication, read fuller work on upaya, raft and ladder metaphors, Hori on koan curricula, Sells on unsaying, Smith on Nagarjuna and Wittgenstein, Dogen scholarship on practice-realization, Shinran scholarship on Other Power, Pargament on agency styles, and Hadot on spiritual exercises.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.json:137:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike MN 22, upaya, Sells, Smith, Dogen scholarship, and prior Lumenary custody models, this idea's possible contribution is a bounded two-variable after-use rubric that predicts when a practitioner should keep a method, set it down, or let it appear as conduct, especially for achievement-driven people who turn tools into proof of worth."
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-first-ask-what-the-words-do-5bbc7c109ba18f80.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Direct-recognition and practice-realization lineages, such as Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out, Dogen practice-realization, and Pure Land Other Power.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-first-ask-what-the-words-do-5bbc7c109ba18f80.json:28:      "expected_observation": "Usable inter-rater agreement on roles such as assertion, instruction, warning, defense, report, repair, praise, direct recognition, and analyst-frame-refused across Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23, SN 22.59, SN 22.95, Udana 1.10, Heart Sutra, Dogen, and one pointing-out manual.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-first-ask-what-the-words-do-5bbc7c109ba18f80.json:36:      "test_surface": "Practitioner interviews with Advaita, Theravada, Dzogchen or Mahamudra, Zen, spiritual direction, and contemplative-science practitioners.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-first-ask-what-the-words-do-5bbc7c109ba18f80.json:57:    "Talal Asad discursive tradition correct practice authorized discourse religion",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-first-ask-what-the-words-do-5bbc7c109ba18f80.json:61:    "Dzogchen pointing out instruction words perform recognition not description",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-first-ask-what-the-words-do-5bbc7c109ba18f80.json:62:    "meditation adverse effects interpretation social support Varieties of Contemplative Experience"
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-first-ask-what-the-words-do-5bbc7c109ba18f80.json:78:      "difference": "Asad is not focused on quiet states or individual post-gap identity verdicts. The candidate converts the insight into a micro-codebook for post-silence language.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-first-ask-what-the-words-do-5bbc7c109ba18f80.json:81:      "source": "Talal Asad, The Idea of an Anthropology of Islam, discursive tradition, https://bpb-ap-se2.wpmucdn.com/thinkspace.csu.edu.au/dist/c/3891/files/2020/10/Asad-Anthropology.pdf"
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-first-ask-what-the-words-do-5bbc7c109ba18f80.json:99:      "source": "Lindahl et al., Varieties of Contemplative Experience, PLOS ONE 2017, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239"
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-first-ask-what-the-words-do-5bbc7c109ba18f80.json:106:    "Add anomaly cases before public use: Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out, Dogen practice-realization, Pure Land Other Power, and competent direct-recognition settings.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-first-ask-what-the-words-do-5bbc7c109ba18f80.json:110:  "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.50 to 0.36. The core structure is known from speech-act theory, religious-language philosophy, Asad, Sharf, Katz-style contextualism, VCE, and prior Lumenary authorization records. Its publishability depends on being presented as a bounded role-check protocol for stable overinterpreters, not as a new doctrine. Human-condition fit is clear but narrow: stable solo practitioners, meditation-app users, cross-tradition readers, reflective professionals, students, and caregivers who turn quiet states or explanations into judgments about identity, failure, progress, or worth. It is not for acute panic, psychosis, mania, dissociation, trauma amnesia, active addiction withdrawal, medical blackout concerns, OCD or scrupulosity reassurance loops, unsafe authority settings, or people already under competent teacher or clinical guidance.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-first-ask-what-the-words-do-5bbc7c109ba18f80.json:125:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with direct introduction",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-first-ask-what-the-words-do-5bbc7c109ba18f80.json:126:      "Zen teachers familiar with Dogen practice-realization",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-first-ask-what-the-words-do-5bbc7c109ba18f80.json:137:    "secondary_literature_gap": "Before publication, search Austin and Searle on speech acts, SEP Religious Language, Lindbeck on doctrine as grammar, Asad on discursive tradition, Sharf on rhetoric of meditative experience, Katz and Proudfoot on mediated religious experience, Taves on experience attribution, Freiberger on comparative method, Buddhist upaya and raft-simile literature, Ignatian discernment, Dogen practice-realization, Pure Land Other Power, and Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out manuals. Also compare internal records: Stratified Post-Negation Authorization, Stop Making Silence Judge You, No Silence Proves Itself, You Cannot Prove the One Who Is Asking, and When Tools Become Judges.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-first-ask-what-the-words-do-5bbc7c109ba18f80.json:150:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Austin, religious-language theory, Asad, Sharf, VCE, and prior Lumenary authorization records, this candidate says the first coding operation after quiet states should be sentence role, before doctrinal inference, neuroscience interpretation, or identity verdict. That is a useful bounded extension, not a standalone discovery."
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-independently-coded-function-by-placement-analysis-plus-post-gap-ad.md:18:**Steelman:** The proponent is not merely saying that no-self traditions secretly need a self. The stronger claim is architectural: any path that dissolves, denies, or transcends ordinary selfhood still has to preserve some functional capacities long enough for training to happen, such as receiving instruction, remembering, correcting error, sustaining attention, and recognizing or integrating change. Different traditions solve this pressure differently, and those solutions should predict their effort theory, verification rules, warnings, and fruit. Buddhism preserves causal process without owner, Advaita preserves deepest identity while dissolving apparent process, Dogen collapses practice and realization, and Sufi fana and baqa bridge self-loss through divine relation.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-independently-coded-function-by-placement-analysis-plus-post-gap-ad.md:24:I concede four things cleanly. First, the distributed-containment model is genuinely better at explaining other-power, devotional, and teacher-field traditions; the original model underweighted these. Second, Engler's clinical formulation covers the safety ground and has priority on the practical insight. Third, the title overstated universality; the claim is graded, not universal. Fourth, the four management strategies are heuristic mixtures, not clean types. What I defend is more specific. The distributed-containment model and the minimum-self model are not competitors. They answer different questions, and the containment model presupposes the functional one. You cannot distribute continuity until you know what must be continued. The functions are: receiving instruction or transmission, sustaining effort or openness, correcting error, and recognizing change. Where these are housed is a second-order question. The irreducible receiving surface is not trivially true. Traditions that push it thinnest, Dzogchen and radical Pure Land, develop the most precise protocols around exactly that thin point. Dzogchen requires a specific relational context, precise timing, and teacher judgment of readiness. Shinran developed elaborate doctrinal machinery to explain how even entrusting is given without self-power. If the receiving surface were trivial, these traditions would not need to engineer around it so carefully. The Engler formulation is sequential: first build ego, then dissolve. The revised minimum-self model is concurrent: a beginning vipassana practitioner needs enough self to sit and follow instructions while those instructions are already framing the self as impersonal aggregates. This is not a before-and-after problem but a during problem that the practice manages at every session. The management strategies, even as heuristics, predict architecture that the containment model alone does not. Tell me a tradition's primary continuity strategy and I can predict its map type, warning profile, and verification method. Causal continuity yields condition-tracking maps (Abhidharma). Ontological identity yields confusion-accounting theory (adhyasa). Temporal collapse resists stage sequencing (Dogen). Divine restoration concentrates teacher authority at the annihilation moment (Sufi sheikh at fana). These predictions require knowing both what continuity function is at stake and what the dissolution target is. Container strength alone cannot generate them. The human-condition revision: the model matters most for people encountering dissolution teachings outside traditional containers. When the container is strong, the practitioner's receiving surface can be thin because the ecology carries load. When the container is weak or absent (app-based meditation, books without teachers, retreat weekends without follow-up, psychedelic experiences without integration), the practitioner's own self-capacity must carry more of the continuity burden. The danger zone is the mismatch: a person with low self-capacity entering a path with weak distributed support, or a person with high self-management entering a strongly distributed path that demands a surrender they cannot give. The primary cohort is secular seekers, trauma survivors drawn to dissolution language, high-achievers approaching practice with optimization mindsets, cross-tradition samplers without sustained teacher relationships, and clinicians or chaplains who need to assess when practice helps versus harms. The non-fit case is practitioners in intact traditional communities where the distributed ecology already manages continuity; for them, the model adds nothing. Also outside scope: acute psychiatric crisis (clinical stabilization, not contemplative architecture) and single-lineage practitioners whose receiving surface and dissolution target are always aligned by design. The deepest crux is whether function-identification adds predictive power beyond placement-identification. If knowing w...
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-one-begins-alone-3260ddf016476c06.md:12:Self-release is risky when a person's steadiness has been held almost entirely by performance and control, unless some ordinary form of care already carries part of life. This support-placement claim should apply only where a path stages a real crossing; no-gap paths such as Dogen-style practice-realization and Huangbo-style no-seeking should be anomaly tests rather than extra boxes in the same table.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-one-begins-alone-3260ddf016476c06.md:26:- Dogen Bendowa, https://www.lionsroar.com/just-wholeheartedly-sit/, and Huangbo transmission and no-seeking scholarship, https://www.mdpi.com/2077-1444/12/4/279, read with Shinran's reply to Senshin, https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-one-begins-alone-3260ddf016476c06.md:28:Structural observation: SN 22.59 stages inquiry, disenchantment, release, and task completion, while SN 45.2 already makes good friendship central to path cultivation. That means no one begins alone is textually old in early Buddhist terms. Dogen's Bendowa makes practice and realization inseparable, yet still stresses master, transmission, trust, and authentic teacher. Huangbo's no-seeking grammar strains the crossing model, but Chan transmission literature shows that no-seeking does not mean absence of teacher, lineage, or interpretive ecology. Shinran relocates efficacy to the Vow and forbids calculation by the practicer. The support contrast is real, but the candidate's no-gap boundary may be more doctrinal than practical.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-one-begins-alone-3260ddf016476c06.md:30:Secondary literature gap: Before any stronger claim, read Clark and Chalmers on extended mind, https://www.consc.net/papers/extended.html; Krueger on extended religious cognition; Pargament on religious coping; attachment secure-base and social baseline theory; AA Twelve Steps and sponsorship literature, https://www.aa.org/the-twelve-steps; VCE and Progress or Pathology; burnout and perfectionism sources, including WHO on burnout, https://www.who.int/standards/classifications/frequently-asked-questions/burn-out-an-occupational-phenomenon, and Curran and Hill, https://eprints.lse.ac.uk/101352/1/Curran_Hill2018.pdf; Dogen scholarship on shusho itto; Chan studies on Huangbo; Shinran scholarship on hakarai and Other Power; and internal Lumenary support-holder records.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-one-begins-alone-3260ddf016476c06.md:38:- Clark Chalmers Extended Mind reliable external supports cognition original paper
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-one-begins-alone-3260ddf016476c06.md:39:- Pargament religious coping self directing collaborative deferring original 1988
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-one-begins-alone-3260ddf016476c06.md:43:- Dogen Bendowa practice realization one Huangbo Transmission of Mind seeking source
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-one-begins-alone-3260ddf016476c06.md:48:- Clark and Chalmers, The Extended Mind, https://www.consc.net/papers/extended.html, with religious-cognition extension by Joel Krueger.: overlap: Close. Reliable external resources, artifacts, practices, people, places, rituals, and material culture can partly constitute cognition and regulation rather than merely assist it.; difference: The candidate applies support externalism to self-release safety and burnout collapse severity.; novelty impact: Strong downgrade for the support ontology. Possible extension remains only in the specific collapse-severity prediction.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-one-begins-alone-3260ddf016476c06.md:49:- Pargament et al. 1988 religious coping styles, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/.: overlap: Very close on responsibility location: self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles already distinguish where problem-solving agency sits.; difference: The candidate widens the holder set beyond God to body, routine, duty, teacher, vow, ritual, community, and care, and adds a no-gap path gate.; novelty impact: Strong downgrade. The broader holder set is useful but not a discovery.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-one-begins-alone-3260ddf016476c06.md:53:- Dogen Bendowa and Soto practice-realization, https://www.lionsroar.com/just-wholeheartedly-sit/, plus Huangbo and Chan transmission scholarship, https://www.mdpi.com/2077-1444/12/4/279.: overlap: The no-gap anomaly is already known: some sources refuse staged attainment or seeking, while still functioning inside teacher, transmission, and practice ecology.; difference: The candidate uses no-gap cases as a scope gate for support-placement coding.; novelty impact: Useful as a guardrail, not as a standalone discovery.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-one-begins-alone-3260ddf016476c06.md:62:Candidate: No-gap traditions may still show the same support-loss failures as staged crossing paths, because Dogen, Huangbo, Dzogchen, and other no-seeking settings still rely on teachers, lineage, vows, rhythms, texts, community, and correction.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-one-begins-alone-3260ddf016476c06.md:71:- If: The no-gap boundary is real rather than analyst convenience. Then: Dogen, Huangbo, and direct-recognition sources should warn mainly against seeking, grasping, staged attainment, and conceptualization, not against losing a carried remainder across a before-after threshold. Weakens if: Held-out manuals and practitioner interviews in no-gap traditions show warning and repair clusters centered on lost teacher, vow, community, ritual, or continuity support, just like staged effort paths. Test surface: Split-source coding of Bendowa, Genjokoan or Uji, Huangbo texts, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra direct-introduction manual, and teacher interviews.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-one-begins-alone-3260ddf016476c06.md:85:- Soto Zen teachers and Dogen scholars
